WEBVTT

00:01.568 --> 00:05.104
[♪]

00:18.418 --> 00:20.452
HERE YOU GO, KID.

00:20.454 --> 00:21.453
THANKS.

00:21.455 --> 00:22.688
YOU KNOW, I HEAR

00:22.690 --> 00:24.356
A LOT OF STORIES
COME OUT OF THAT BACKSEAT,

00:24.358 --> 00:26.425
BUT YOURS IS A DOOZY.

00:26.427 --> 00:28.427
I HAVEN'T TOLD ANYBODY.

00:28.429 --> 00:30.195
I CAN'T BELIEVE I TOLD YOU.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.196
DON'T WORRY,
HONEY.

00:31.198 --> 00:32.431
YOU'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING.

00:32.433 --> 00:35.667
AND MAIL THAT LETTER...

00:35.669 --> 00:38.103
'CAUSE LIFE IS SHORT.

00:38.105 --> 00:39.571
[CHUCKLES] I KNOW.

00:39.573 --> 00:42.541
BUT, UM, I'M SO LATE.

00:42.543 --> 00:44.309
COULD YOU...?

00:44.311 --> 00:45.577
YEAH.

00:45.579 --> 00:48.213
NO PROBLEM.
ALL PART OF THE SERVICE.

00:48.215 --> 00:50.182
TAXI. HEY!

00:50.184 --> 00:52.284
UH, WE'RE GOING
TO THE OXFORD.

00:52.286 --> 00:54.520
WELL, GET IN.

00:56.689 --> 00:59.625
[♪]

01:03.096 --> 01:06.198
[WOMAN]: OKAY, YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO BELIEVE THIS.

01:06.200 --> 01:08.233
HE MISSED THE TRAIN.

01:08.235 --> 01:10.502
I KNOW.

01:10.504 --> 01:12.337
NO, HE'LL BE OKAY.

01:12.339 --> 01:16.108
HE'S GOING TO CATCH THE 2:00,
SO I'M JUST LETTING YOU KNOW.

01:16.110 --> 01:17.476
I'M FINE.

01:17.478 --> 01:18.444
BUT YOU'LL HAVE TO
KEEP EVERYBODY THERE

01:18.446 --> 01:19.511
UNTIL WE GET BACK.

01:19.513 --> 01:21.113
SORRY.

01:21.115 --> 01:22.648
COULD I MAIL THIS LETTER?

01:22.650 --> 01:24.616
YEAH, WHATEVER.

01:24.618 --> 01:25.684
I DON'T KNOW.

01:25.686 --> 01:27.553
YOU CAN FEED THEM WHENEVER.

01:27.555 --> 01:30.722
PERFECT. AND THERE'S
SOME SALSA IN THE FRIDGE.

01:30.724 --> 01:32.658
DO YOU KNOW...

01:32.660 --> 01:37.262
[♪]

01:37.264 --> 01:38.464
YEAH. OKAY.

01:38.466 --> 01:40.799
THAT'S GREAT...

01:48.141 --> 01:51.643
[OLIVER]: <i>SOMETIMES, I WONDER</i>
<i>WHO MAILED THE FIRST LETTER.</i>

01:51.645 --> 01:55.447
<i>WHO WAS THAT BRAVE SOUL</i>
<i>WHO PUT A STAMP ON AN ENVELOPE,</i>

01:55.449 --> 01:57.382
AND RELEASED IT INTO THE WORLD,

01:57.384 --> 01:59.182
<i>TRUSTING A STRANGER</i>

01:59.184 --> 02:02.654
<i>TO DELIVER IT ACROSS THE MILES</i>
<i>AND ACROSS TIME.</i>

02:02.656 --> 02:05.324
<i>IN THIS NEW WORLD</i>
<i>OF INSTANT REPLIES</i>

02:05.326 --> 02:06.391
<i>AND CASUAL DELETING,</i>

02:06.393 --> 02:07.691
<i>WHAT I LOVE ABOUT MY WORK IS,</i>

02:07.693 --> 02:10.162
<i>I CAN HOLD A LETTER,</i>
<i>A REAL LETTER, IN MY HAND,</i>

02:10.164 --> 02:12.731
<i>AND BE THAT STRANGER</i>
<i>WHOSE SOLE MISSION--</i>

02:12.733 --> 02:13.732
NEXT!

02:13.734 --> 02:15.501
YES. UH...

02:15.503 --> 02:18.504
I'D LIKE A CUP OF COFFEE.

02:18.506 --> 02:19.671
"ASPEN," "VAIL,"
OR "STEAMBOAT"?

02:19.673 --> 02:21.440
I'M SORRY,
I'M NOT FOLLOWING?

02:21.442 --> 02:23.742
SMALL, MEDIUM,
OR LARGE?

02:23.744 --> 02:25.310
OH, LARGE. LARGE COFFEE.

02:25.312 --> 02:27.546
RIGHT. UH...
WHICH COFFEE?

02:27.548 --> 02:29.715
UH, WHAT DO YOU RECOMMEND?

02:29.717 --> 02:32.551
EVERYTHING'S
ON THE BOARD.

02:32.553 --> 02:34.553
THIS IS MY FIRST VISIT.

02:34.555 --> 02:36.288
FRANKLY, I WOULDN'T
BE HERE AT ALL

02:36.290 --> 02:39.291
IF MY COFFEE MACHINE HADN'T BEEN
ILLEGALLY APPROPRIATED

02:39.293 --> 02:41.627
AFTER AN UNFORTUNATE
WAR OF WORDS WITH MY SUPERIOR.

02:41.629 --> 02:43.295
WELL, I WOULDN'T CALL HER
MY SUPERIOR EXAC--

02:43.297 --> 02:44.296
EXCUSE ME?

02:44.298 --> 02:45.364
COULD I JUST
GIVE HIM MY ORDER

02:45.366 --> 02:46.465
WHILE YOU'RE REMINISCING?

02:46.467 --> 02:47.599
I'LL EVEN PAY
FOR YOUR COFFEE,

02:47.601 --> 02:49.201
IF YOU JUST LET ME
GO AHEAD OF YOU.

02:49.203 --> 02:50.501
BE MY GUEST.

02:50.503 --> 02:54.239
SORRY. IT'S JUST I'M LATE,
IT'S MY FIRST DAY AT MY NEW JOB.

02:54.241 --> 02:55.541
WELL, AT LEAST
YOU'RE EMPLOYED.

02:55.543 --> 02:57.242
ASPEN "SKINNY" VANILLA LATTE.

02:57.244 --> 02:58.644
INSTEAD OF JUST
SITTING OVER THERE

02:58.646 --> 03:00.245
STARING OFF
INTO CYBERSPACE.

03:00.247 --> 03:01.580
HE'LL HAVE
A STEAMBOAT AMERICANO.

03:01.582 --> 03:04.216
WHAT IS THAT?

03:04.218 --> 03:06.318
LARGE BLACK COFFEE.

03:06.320 --> 03:08.220
AH!

03:08.222 --> 03:10.689
MOST OF THOSE PEOPLE
ACTUALLY ARE EMPLOYED.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.624
THEY'RE JUST
WORKING FROM HOME.

03:12.626 --> 03:14.593
THEORETICALLY.

03:14.595 --> 03:17.462
AND SOMEONE PAYS THEM?
THEORETICALLY?

03:18.565 --> 03:20.232
ASPEN SKINNY VANILLA LATTE...

03:20.234 --> 03:22.634
AND A STEAMBOAT AMERICANO.

03:22.636 --> 03:25.771
GOTTA GO.
KEEP THE CHANGE.

03:28.308 --> 03:29.675
THANKS.

03:32.345 --> 03:33.344
<i>THERE IT IS--</i>

03:33.346 --> 03:35.514
<i>A BEACON OF HOPE TO THOSE</i>
<i>WHO STILL PUT THEIR FAITH</i>

03:35.516 --> 03:37.649
<i>IN THE POWER</i>
<i>OF A PIECE OF PAPER</i>

03:37.651 --> 03:39.618
<i>AND A 46-CENT STAMP.</i>

03:39.620 --> 03:40.818
<i>AND BEHIND EVERY LETTER</i>

03:40.820 --> 03:42.788
<i>STAND THOUSANDS</i>
<i>OF DEDICATED HEROES,</i>

03:42.790 --> 03:45.657
<i>WHO STILL FIGHT THE GOOD FIGHT</i>
<i>THROUGH RAIN AND SNOW</i>

03:45.659 --> 03:47.492
<i>AND FISCAL CLIFFS</i>

03:47.494 --> 03:49.661
<i>TO DELIVER EVERY NOTE,</i>
<i>EVERY CARD, EVERY LETTER.</i>

03:49.663 --> 03:50.696
MORNING, NORMAN.

03:50.698 --> 03:51.897
MORNING, OLIVER.

03:51.899 --> 03:54.533
[OLIVER]:
<i>...AND I AM ONE OF THEM--</i>

03:54.535 --> 03:55.667
<i>THE FEW...</i>

03:55.669 --> 03:56.802
<i>THE PROUD...</i>

03:56.804 --> 03:58.770
<i>THE POSTAL.</i>

03:58.772 --> 04:02.407
<i>I WORK FOR YOU,</i>
<i>WHOEVER YOU ARE,</i>

04:02.409 --> 04:04.476
<i>OR WHOEVER YOU WERE.</i>

04:05.511 --> 04:07.646
I TOLD YOU,
THIS IS A MISTAKE.

04:07.648 --> 04:10.315
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE ASSIGNED
TO DIRECT LINE OPERATIONS

04:10.317 --> 04:12.417
AS A TECHNICAL
SYSTEMS CONSULTANT.

04:12.419 --> 04:14.786
IT SAYS RIGHT HERE
THAT YOU ARE D.L.O.

04:14.788 --> 04:16.521
YEAH. "DIRECT
LINE OPERATIONS."

04:16.523 --> 04:17.823
THAT'S WHAT WASHINGTON
IS NOW CALLING

04:17.825 --> 04:19.691
COMPUTER-MANAGED
DELIVERY SERVICES.

04:19.693 --> 04:21.627
WELL, WE'RE STILL CALLING IT THE
"DEAD LETTER OFFICE."

04:21.629 --> 04:22.928
LOOK, IF YOU JUST
CALL THE PG'S OFFICE--

04:22.930 --> 04:24.563
-...IN WASHINGTON AND...
-THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

04:24.565 --> 04:26.398
I'LL CALL THE POSTMASTER GENERAL

04:26.400 --> 04:29.501
RIGHT AFTER I RETURN THAT CALL
FROM THE SECRETARY OF DEFENSE.

04:29.503 --> 04:31.570
OKAY. THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

04:31.572 --> 04:32.838
I DON'T BELONG HERE.

04:32.840 --> 04:35.774
YOU WAIT RIGHT HERE.

04:39.545 --> 04:40.779
OLIVER!

04:40.781 --> 04:42.814
I WANT YOU
TO TRAIN THIS GIRL.

04:42.816 --> 04:44.583
SHE'S A COMPUTER-SOMETHING
FROM WASHINGTON.

04:44.585 --> 04:45.484
NO.

04:45.486 --> 04:46.685
I WILL FIRE YOU.

04:46.687 --> 04:48.353
I HAVE A GOVERNMENT
SERVICE PAY LEVEL

04:48.355 --> 04:49.454
HIGHER THAN YOU CAN COUNT.

04:49.456 --> 04:51.423
I WILL TAKE AWAY
YOUR REFRIGERATOR.

04:51.425 --> 04:53.425
YOU WILL RETURN
MY MR. COFFEE.

04:53.427 --> 04:55.861
[CLEARS HER THROAT]

04:57.864 --> 04:59.464
DONE.

04:59.466 --> 05:00.599
SEND HER IN.

05:02.635 --> 05:04.002
McINERNEY!

05:08.841 --> 05:10.409
IT'S YOU.

05:12.445 --> 05:15.480
MR. STEAMBOAT.
INCREDIBLE.

05:15.482 --> 05:18.450
YOU KNOW
EACH OTHER?

05:18.452 --> 05:20.619
[BOTH AT SAME TIME]:
THEORETICALLY.

05:25.758 --> 05:28.527
[♪]

05:36.736 --> 05:39.705
RITA, NORMAN...
OUR RANKS HAVE BEEN INCREASED.

05:39.707 --> 05:40.872
THIS IS--

05:40.874 --> 05:43.008
THIS IS...?

05:43.010 --> 05:44.776
IS?

05:44.778 --> 05:46.478
I'M SHANE McINERNEY.

05:47.714 --> 05:48.914
[OLIVER SCOFFS]

05:48.916 --> 05:51.616
I CAN'T WORK
WITH SOMEONE NAMED SHANE.

05:51.618 --> 05:52.884
NORMAN?

05:52.886 --> 05:54.453
TELL HER WHY.

05:54.455 --> 05:56.488
I GOT IT.
BECAUSE, UH, AT SOME POINT,

05:56.490 --> 05:58.857
YOU, SHANE, WILL WALK AWAY,

05:58.859 --> 06:01.727
AND OLIVER
WILL NEED YOU TO-- RETURN?

06:01.729 --> 06:04.029
VERY GOOD, GO ON.

06:04.031 --> 06:05.831
AND OLIVER WILL BE
FORCED TO SAY--

06:05.833 --> 06:08.500
[THEATRICALLY]:
"SHANE! COME BACK, SHANE!"

06:08.502 --> 06:10.502
AT WHICH POINT,
YOU WILL LOOK AT ME

06:10.504 --> 06:13.905
WITH MUCH THE SAME VACANCY
WITH WHICH YOU STARE AT ME NOW,

06:13.907 --> 06:15.874
UTTERLY UNAWARE

06:15.876 --> 06:18.577
OF THE UNFORTUNATE
CINEMATIC REFERENCE.

06:18.579 --> 06:20.512
THEREFORE,
I SHALL CALL YOU...

06:20.514 --> 06:21.747
TSK...

06:21.749 --> 06:23.749
[TAKES A BREATH]

06:24.817 --> 06:26.585
"SHERYL."

06:27.720 --> 06:29.020
SHERYL?

06:29.022 --> 06:30.922
WELL... [CHUCKLES]
I'M JUST HERE TEMPORARILY--

06:30.924 --> 06:32.624
AND HOW WISE OF YOU

06:32.626 --> 06:34.793
TO REALIZE SUCH A GREAT TRUTH
SO EARLY ON IN LIFE.

06:34.795 --> 06:37.662
WHAT I MEAN IS,
THERE'S BEEN A MISTAKE.

06:37.664 --> 06:38.730
A MERRY MIX-UP, PERHAPS.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.832
A MISTAKE?
WELL, WE SHALL SEE.

06:40.834 --> 06:43.101
RITA, PLEASE FILE THIS
IN A SAFE PLACE.

06:44.604 --> 06:46.471
A PHOTOGRAPHIC MEMORY

06:46.473 --> 06:48.640
IS A PLUS
IN THIS BUSINESS.

06:51.477 --> 06:55.847
I BELIEVE THERE ARE
NO COINCIDENCES, MS. McINERNEY.

06:55.849 --> 07:00.018
COINCIDENCE IS
THE MIDDLE NAME OF THE ALMIGHTY.

07:00.987 --> 07:02.921
YOU DID THAT?

07:02.923 --> 07:06.525
NO. BUT IT IS A STANDARD
TO WHICH WE ASPIRE,

07:06.527 --> 07:08.059
AND, ONE DAY,
WE, TOO, SHALL JOIN

07:08.061 --> 07:10.061
THE PANTHEON
OF POSTAL EXCELLENCE. HMM?

07:12.665 --> 07:13.664
EVERY LETTER

07:13.666 --> 07:15.967
THAT PASSES THROUGH
THE UNITED STATES POSTAL SYSTEM

07:15.969 --> 07:18.503
REPRESENTS AN ACT OF FAITH.

07:18.505 --> 07:21.740
FAITH THAT IT WILL
REACH ITS DESTINATION

07:21.742 --> 07:23.074
ON TIME
AND IN GOOD CONDITION.

07:23.076 --> 07:26.011
FAITH THAT WHAT WAS WRITTEN
BY THE WRITER

07:26.013 --> 07:29.915
SHALL REMAIN PRIVATE
UNTIL READ BY THE...?

07:31.584 --> 07:32.784
WRITE-EE?

07:32.786 --> 07:33.919
THIS IS A SACRED COVENANT

07:33.921 --> 07:36.488
THAT, IF BROKEN, SIGNALS WHAT?

07:36.490 --> 07:37.989
NORMAN?

07:37.991 --> 07:40.058
"THE BREAKDOWN OF CIVILIZATION
AND THE BEGINNING OF ANARCHY."

07:40.060 --> 07:42.627
THIS IS WHY WE ATTEMPT
TO ASCERTAIN THE CORRECT ADDRESS

07:42.629 --> 07:44.729
USING CLUES ON
THE OUTSIDE OF THE ENVELOPE

07:44.731 --> 07:46.665
UNTIL WE HAVE NO OTHER CHOICE.

07:46.667 --> 07:48.967
AND IT IS THAT MOMENT
WHEN WE DECIDE

07:48.969 --> 07:50.135
TO OPEN THE LETTER.

07:50.137 --> 07:52.838
WE DO IT REVERENTLY,
RESPECTFULLY,

07:52.840 --> 07:56.842
MUCH LIKE A MEDICAL STUDENT
PERFORMING A FIRST AUTOPSY.

07:56.844 --> 07:58.677
OH, GOD HELP ME.

07:58.679 --> 08:00.745
WE READ ONLY
AS FAR AS WE MUST,

08:00.747 --> 08:03.882
GLEANING AND GATHERING CLUES
AS TO THE CORRECT DESTINATION.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.717
THIS...

08:05.719 --> 08:07.953
IS A HIGH CALLING, INDEED,
SHERYL.

08:07.955 --> 08:10.689
SHANE. IT'S SHANE.

08:11.958 --> 08:14.059
NOW IT'S TIME
FOR SOME REAL WORK.

08:14.061 --> 08:17.128
[♪]

08:21.534 --> 08:23.869
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

08:25.605 --> 08:26.938
AH. FIRST NAME INTACT.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.073
THOMAS.

08:28.075 --> 08:31.042
P-E-R-- SOMETHING.

08:31.044 --> 08:33.645
UH, CARD HAS BEEN RIPPED BY...
[SNIFFING]

08:33.647 --> 08:34.846
CANINE.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.047
SEATTLE POSTMARK.

08:36.049 --> 08:37.816
NOT A BIRTHDAY CARD.

08:37.818 --> 08:39.651
NOT A SYMPATHY CARD.

08:40.186 --> 08:41.920
I'M GUESSING...

08:41.922 --> 08:43.622
"THINKING OF YOU."

08:43.624 --> 08:45.724
ALRIGHT...

08:45.726 --> 08:47.626
WE'RE GOING IN.

08:48.694 --> 08:51.563
[♪]

08:51.565 --> 08:53.765
[DOOR SWINGS OPEN]

08:54.734 --> 08:55.734
McINERNEY.

08:55.736 --> 08:57.569
GUESS WHAT?

08:57.571 --> 08:59.804
THERE IS SOMETHING IN THE SYSTEM
CALLED DIRECT LINE OPERATIONS.

08:59.806 --> 09:01.806
-I KNOW.
-BUT IT'S NOT HERE...

09:01.808 --> 09:02.908
IT'S IN NORTHGLENN.

09:02.910 --> 09:04.976
GREAT! I'M ON MY WAY.

09:04.978 --> 09:06.044
NAH. NOT SO FAST, MISSY.

09:06.046 --> 09:08.213
YOU GOTTA APPLY FOR REASSIGNMENT

09:08.215 --> 09:09.848
AND KEEP WORKING HERE
FOR SIX WEEKS

09:09.850 --> 09:11.716
BEFORE WE APPROVE YOU
FOR TRANSFER.

09:11.718 --> 09:13.852
[LAUGHING] TRANSFER?

09:13.854 --> 09:16.855
YOU'RE JOKING... RIGHT?

09:19.926 --> 09:21.192
[SIGHS]

09:21.194 --> 09:23.895
[PEN SCRATCHING PAGE]

09:26.933 --> 09:28.733
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

09:28.735 --> 09:30.168
[OLIVER]: HARD TO BELIEVE
SHE WAS ONCE

09:30.170 --> 09:32.938
"MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY"
OF 1999, HMM?

09:32.940 --> 09:35.874
SHALL WE CONTINUE?

09:36.876 --> 09:39.945
[♪]

09:41.981 --> 09:43.815
"LET'S CATCH UP.

09:43.817 --> 09:46.751
DROPPED BY 'CURIOS' YESTERDAY,
BUT YOU WERE ON A BREAK, SO--"

09:46.753 --> 09:47.819
NORMAN?

09:47.821 --> 09:49.054
"CURIOS." I'M ON IT.

09:49.056 --> 09:50.055
SEATTLE.

09:50.057 --> 09:51.656
YOU GUYS DO KNOW

09:51.658 --> 09:54.125
THAT WE ARE IN
THE 21st CENTURY, RIGHT?

09:54.127 --> 09:57.062
BETTER LOOK AT
"ANTIQUE STORES"

09:57.064 --> 09:58.863
AND "GIFT SHOPS."

09:58.865 --> 10:02.000
NO, I'VE GOT THIS.
GOOGLING "CURIOS, SEATTLE."

10:02.002 --> 10:03.001
CURIOS ANTIQUES.

10:03.003 --> 10:04.169
PROPRIETOR:
THOMAS PERKINS.

10:04.171 --> 10:06.938
"P-E-R."

10:08.107 --> 10:09.641
THAT'S IMPRESSIVE.

10:09.643 --> 10:10.809
CHILD'S PLAY.

10:10.811 --> 10:14.079
[♪]

10:22.154 --> 10:24.756
THANK YOU, RITA.

10:29.161 --> 10:31.129
[VACUUM WHOOSHES]

10:31.131 --> 10:32.864
MOVING ON.

10:32.866 --> 10:36.668
SO, WHAT, YOU JUST
REACH IN AND GRAB ONE?

10:36.670 --> 10:38.169
THERE'S NO SYSTEM?
NO PROTOCOL?

10:38.171 --> 10:39.838
WELL, AS I SAID,

10:39.840 --> 10:43.008
THERE'S SOMETHING DIVINE
AT WORK HERE, MS. McINERNEY.

10:43.010 --> 10:45.744
WE DO NOT FIND THE LETTERS
THAT MUST BE FOUND TODAY.

10:45.746 --> 10:47.312
<i>THEY</i> FIND US.

10:47.314 --> 10:50.281
AND YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT?

10:50.283 --> 10:51.950
TAKE TODAY, FOR EXAMPLE.

10:51.952 --> 10:53.184
OF ALL THE COFFEE SHOPS

10:53.186 --> 10:54.786
IN ALL THE TOWNS
IN ALL THE WORLD...

10:54.788 --> 10:56.187
YOU WALKED INTO MINE.

10:56.189 --> 10:57.689
YES! AND JUST AS

10:57.691 --> 10:58.923
EVERYTHING
IN THE DEAD LETTER OFFICE

10:58.925 --> 11:00.825
WAS ORIGINALLY INTENDED
FOR SOMEPLACE ELSE,

11:00.827 --> 11:03.862
AND YET, FOR
SOME PROVIDENTIAL REASON,

11:03.864 --> 11:05.797
THEY HAVE BEEN MISDIRECTED.

11:05.799 --> 11:07.298
TEMPORARILY, OF COURSE.

11:07.300 --> 11:09.868
NOT UNLIKE YOU.

11:10.803 --> 11:13.238
[♪]

11:13.240 --> 11:14.939
-BUT I--
-SHH...

11:14.941 --> 11:16.708
IT'S HAPPENING.

11:16.710 --> 11:19.244
NORMAN,
GET YOUR PENCIL, PLEASE.

11:21.981 --> 11:25.750
ADDRESSED TO "CHARLIE,"
NO SURNAME.

11:25.752 --> 11:27.786
REPLY READS SIMPLY,

11:27.788 --> 11:29.788
"KELLY
FROM WASHINGTON PARK."

11:29.790 --> 11:32.824
MM. 45-CENT
BICYCLE COMMEMORATIVE.

11:32.826 --> 11:34.159
I USED TO RIDE BIKES IN
WASHINGTON PARK ALL THE TIME!

11:34.161 --> 11:35.994
THERE'S A FUNNY
LITTLE MAN THERE

11:35.996 --> 11:37.829
NAMED "STUMPY,"
HE RENTS SCHWINNS.

11:37.831 --> 11:39.964
[OLIVER]: SO A SENTIMENTAL
STAMP CHOICE, THEN?

11:39.966 --> 11:41.032
YES.

11:41.034 --> 11:42.300
SHE ENCLOSED
SOMETHING HERE.

11:42.302 --> 11:44.803
NORMAN,
A CONSULT, PLEASE?

11:46.739 --> 11:49.007
AH. YEAH. WELL,
THE HANDWRITING INDICATES

11:49.009 --> 11:50.141
<i>A FEMALE IN HER 20s.</i>

11:50.143 --> 11:52.077
<i>USUALLY CONFIDENT,</i>

11:52.079 --> 11:54.012
<i>RECENTLY TROUBLED,</i>

11:54.014 --> 11:57.048
<i>INDICATED BY BOLD FIGURES,</i>

11:57.050 --> 11:59.050
<i>TEMPERED WITH</i>
<i>TENTATIVE STROKES.</i>

11:59.052 --> 12:02.153
<i>A LETTER WRITTEN IN A HURRY.</i>

12:02.155 --> 12:05.056
[♪]

12:08.761 --> 12:10.929
"JUNE 26th.

12:10.931 --> 12:14.032
DEAR CHARLIE..."

12:15.901 --> 12:17.969
POSTMARK'S MAY 22nd.

12:17.971 --> 12:19.237
THIS LETTER'S ALMOST A YEAR OLD.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.339
IT NEVER ENTERED THE SYSTEM.

12:21.341 --> 12:22.373
UNTIL A WEEK AGO?

12:22.375 --> 12:23.374
A FLOATER.

12:23.376 --> 12:24.809
WE HAVE A FLOATER!

12:24.811 --> 12:26.077
"DEAR CHARLIE--

12:26.079 --> 12:27.378
"I WANTED TO BE SURE
YOU GOT YOUR BUTTON BACK.

12:27.380 --> 12:29.848
AND I WANTED TO EXPLAIN
ABOUT LAST NIGHT."

12:29.850 --> 12:30.882
OH, DEAR.

12:30.884 --> 12:32.250
ANOTHER ONE OF THOSE

12:32.252 --> 12:34.385
"I CAN EXPLAIN EVERYTHING"
APOLOGETICS,

12:34.387 --> 12:37.155
REPLETE WITH THE RETURN
OF AN ARTICLE OF CLOTHING.

12:37.157 --> 12:39.858
THESE LETTERS
ARE USUALLY ACCOMPANIED BY

12:39.860 --> 12:44.028
LIBERAL REFERENCES
TO JELL-O SHOTS AND TEQUILA.

12:44.030 --> 12:46.131
WELL, SO MUCH
FOR DIVINE INTERVENTION.

12:46.133 --> 12:47.365
"DEAR CHARLIE,

12:47.367 --> 12:49.134
"I WANTED TO BE SURE
YOU GOT YOUR BUTTON BACK.

12:49.136 --> 12:50.835
"I WANTED TO EXPLAIN
ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

12:50.837 --> 12:53.872
WALKING AWAY..."
[VOICE TRAILS OFF]

12:54.907 --> 12:57.408
OH, GOOD HEAVENS.

12:57.410 --> 13:00.245
[♪]

13:07.353 --> 13:09.020
"WALKING AWAY

13:09.022 --> 13:10.388
"AND LEAVING YOU
STANDING IN THE PARK

13:10.390 --> 13:12.123
"WAS THE HARDEST THING
I'VE EVER DONE,

13:12.125 --> 13:14.359
"EXCEPT TO TELL YOU
WHAT I'M GOING TO SAY NEXT.

13:14.361 --> 13:16.060
"I HAD TO LEAVE

13:16.062 --> 13:18.229
"BECAUSE I COULDN'T LET YOU

13:18.231 --> 13:20.365
WATCH ME DIE."

13:22.368 --> 13:23.902
NORMAN...

13:25.905 --> 13:28.273
I THINK I'M GONNA NEED
ANOTHER YOO-HOO.

13:32.344 --> 13:36.481
[♪]

13:42.388 --> 13:43.888
WHAT IS THAT?

13:43.890 --> 13:45.089
[RITA]: YOO-HOO.

13:45.091 --> 13:47.025
HE HARDLY EVER HAS
TWO BEFORE NOON.

13:47.027 --> 13:49.460
I ONCE MET THE PRESIDENT
OF THE YOO-HOO COMPANY

13:49.462 --> 13:51.496
ON A BUS TRIP TO MEXICO.

13:51.498 --> 13:53.131
OKAY.

13:53.133 --> 13:54.199
NOW WHERE WERE WE?

13:54.201 --> 13:55.400
UM, "I HAD TO LEAVE

13:55.402 --> 13:57.902
BECAUSE I COULDN'T LET YOU
WATCH ME DIE."

13:57.904 --> 13:59.370
UH...

13:59.372 --> 14:03.007
OH, YES. HERE WE ARE.
"THE TRUTH IS, I'M SICK--"

14:03.009 --> 14:04.375
[KELLY, WRITING]:
<i>"...I'M REALLY SICK, CHARLIE,</i>

14:04.377 --> 14:05.775
<i>"AND FOR THE LONGEST TIME,</i>

14:05.777 --> 14:09.147
<i>"ALL I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT</i>
<i>IS JUST TRYING TO STAY ALIVE.</i>

14:09.149 --> 14:10.882
<i>"AND THEN, YESTERDAY,</i>

14:10.884 --> 14:14.953
<i>I STEPPED INTO THAT ELEVATOR,</i>
<i>AND THERE YOU WERE."</i>

14:16.455 --> 14:18.056
SORRY.
WE'RE GOING UP.

14:18.058 --> 14:20.058
LOOKS LIKE
ALL THE WAY.

14:20.060 --> 14:22.994
OH, WELL.
DOESN'T REALLY MATTER.

14:22.996 --> 14:25.029
IT'S A NICE RIDE, THOUGH.

14:25.031 --> 14:28.066
YOU GET TO STOP
AT ALL THE BEST FLOORS.

14:28.068 --> 14:30.201
[DOORS DING]

14:31.303 --> 14:33.204
WELL, NOT
ALL THE BEST FLOORS.

14:41.280 --> 14:42.480
CHARLIE,
IS THAT YOU BACK THERE?

14:42.482 --> 14:44.382
GOOD MORNING,
MR. CAMERON.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.517
YOU GET
MY CINNAMON CRULLER?

14:46.519 --> 14:47.518
UH, YES, SIR.

14:47.520 --> 14:49.153
AND THE COLOMBIAN SUPREMO,

14:49.155 --> 14:51.122
NOT THAT JUNK FROM ECUADOR
YOU GOT YESTERDAY?

14:51.124 --> 14:52.257
MM-HMM.

14:52.259 --> 14:54.158
YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA MAKE IT

14:54.160 --> 14:55.526
IN MERGERS AND ACQUISITIONS

14:55.528 --> 14:58.096
IF YOU CAN'T EVEN TAKE
A DECENT COFFEE ORDER, PAL.

14:58.098 --> 15:00.098
[DERISIVE LAUGHTER]

15:00.100 --> 15:02.066
COLOMBIAN. I GOT IT.

15:02.068 --> 15:07.005
MAKE SURE IT'S UP ON THE 17th
BY THE TIME I GET THERE.

15:07.007 --> 15:08.973
OH...

15:08.975 --> 15:10.441
AND, UH, CHARLIE?

15:10.443 --> 15:12.944
TRY NOT TO SCREW UP
LIKE YOU USUALLY DO.

15:12.946 --> 15:14.078
OKAY? I'M MEETING
THAT NEW VP TODAY,

15:14.080 --> 15:15.380
AND I HEAR
SHE LIKES HER DONUTS.

15:15.382 --> 15:17.248
I BET SHE'S A PIG, HUH?

15:17.250 --> 15:19.083
ACTUALLY, I LIKE BAGELS,

15:19.085 --> 15:23.187
BUT, UM, I CAN BUY THEM
FOR MYSELF, RIGHT, CHARLIE?

15:23.189 --> 15:24.989
[LAUGHING]

15:24.991 --> 15:27.125
DID YOU SEE THE LOOK
ON HIS FACE?

15:27.127 --> 15:28.192
[CHUCKLING]

15:28.194 --> 15:29.494
SO YOU'RE THE NEW
VICE-PRESIDENT?

15:29.496 --> 15:32.196
UH, PFFT, NO. DO I LOOK
LIKE A VICE-PRESIDENT?

15:32.198 --> 15:33.564
NO, YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

15:33.566 --> 15:35.500
[STAMMERS]
I, UM--

15:35.502 --> 15:38.202
UH, I MEAN, YOU LOOK--
YOU LOOK GREAT.

15:38.204 --> 15:39.470
WELL, I HOPE I DON'T
GET YOU IN TROUBLE.

15:39.472 --> 15:40.538
I JUST COULDN'T RESIST.

15:40.540 --> 15:42.140
YOU ACTUALLY WORK
FOR THAT JERK?

15:42.142 --> 15:44.242
YEAH, AND THREE MORE
JUST LIKE HIM.

15:44.244 --> 15:45.543
SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

15:45.545 --> 15:47.979
YEAH, WELL, YOU LEARN SOMETHING
FROM EVERYBODY,

15:47.981 --> 15:49.480
EVEN IF IT'S WHAT NOT TO DO.

15:49.482 --> 15:52.317
THAT'S A GREAT ATTITUDE.

15:53.552 --> 15:55.086
WANT A DONUT?

15:55.088 --> 15:57.989
THANKS, BUT I ACTUALLY
DO PREFER BAGELS.

15:57.991 --> 15:59.590
I'M SUPPOSED TO STAY OFF SUGAR
WHILE I'M...

15:59.592 --> 16:00.625
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

16:00.627 --> 16:02.360
OOH. AH, 17.

16:02.362 --> 16:03.594
THANKS AGAIN.

16:03.596 --> 16:05.630
THAT'S THE BEST LAUGH
I'VE HAD ALL WEEK.

16:05.632 --> 16:09.100
MAYBE ALL MONTH.
MAYBE ALL YEAR.

16:09.102 --> 16:11.069
UH, CHARLIE?

16:11.071 --> 16:13.204
YOU DESERVE BETTER.

16:13.206 --> 16:15.139
LIFE IS SHORT.

16:15.141 --> 16:19.344
YEAH, BUT, UH, SOMETIMES,
THE DAYS ARE REALLY LONG.

16:22.247 --> 16:24.215
OH! HEY.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

16:24.217 --> 16:26.384
KELLY!

16:26.386 --> 16:28.453
A NICE IRISH NAME,
KELLY WITH A "Y."

16:28.455 --> 16:30.254
AND CORRECTLY SPELLED.
LOOK AT THAT.

16:30.256 --> 16:31.556
WHY DO PARENTS INSIST ON

16:31.558 --> 16:33.491
BEING UNNECESSARILY CREATIVE
THESE DAYS?

16:33.493 --> 16:36.227
"KELLI" WITH AN "I",
"KELLIE" WITH "I-E",

16:36.229 --> 16:37.362
"KELLYE" WITH "Y-E".

16:37.364 --> 16:40.131
SO HE JUST LEFT HER
IN THE ELEVATOR?

16:40.133 --> 16:42.200
UH, YES.

16:42.202 --> 16:45.103
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

16:49.141 --> 16:52.443
[♪]

16:53.479 --> 16:55.046
HEY!

16:55.048 --> 16:57.048
-HI.
-KELLY.

16:57.050 --> 16:58.049
GOING DOWN?

16:58.051 --> 17:00.618
ALL THE WAY.
I JUST QUIT.

17:02.721 --> 17:06.424
WHOO! FREE AT LAST!
FREE AT LAST!

17:06.426 --> 17:08.159
WAS IT REALLY
THAT BAD?

17:08.161 --> 17:09.494
AH! IT WAS SO BAD,

17:09.496 --> 17:11.195
I TOLD MYSELF
THIS MORNING

17:11.197 --> 17:13.297
IF A BEAUTIFUL GIRL DOESN'T
WALK INTO THIS ELEVATOR

17:13.299 --> 17:14.432
AND RESCUE ME,

17:14.434 --> 17:15.600
I AM RIDING
ALL THE WAY TO THE TOP

17:15.602 --> 17:17.235
AND I AM JUMPING OFF--

17:17.237 --> 17:18.369
DONUTS, COFFEE, AND ALL.

17:18.371 --> 17:19.537
COLOMBIAN COFFEE, I HOPE.

17:19.539 --> 17:20.638
ABSOLUTELY.

17:20.640 --> 17:22.273
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.

17:22.275 --> 17:23.641
I HOPE YOU FIND ANOTHER JOB
THAT YOU LIKE.

17:23.643 --> 17:25.710
THAT'S TOMORROW.

17:25.712 --> 17:28.579
TODAY, I AM TAKING YOU
OUT FOR A BAGEL.

17:28.581 --> 17:30.148
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

17:30.150 --> 17:31.382
WHAT?
YOU GOTTA WORK?

17:31.384 --> 17:32.550
WELL, NO, BUT--

17:32.552 --> 17:33.584
WELL, COME ON!

17:33.586 --> 17:35.486
YOU JUST SAVED
A MAN'S LIFE.

17:35.488 --> 17:36.621
IN SOME CULTURES,

17:36.623 --> 17:38.189
THAT MAKES ME
RESPONSIBLE FOR YOU.

17:38.191 --> 17:40.191
ACTUALLY, I THINK
IT'S THE OTHER WAY AROUND.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.593
EVEN BETTER.
HOW CAN YOU SAY "NO" NOW?

17:42.595 --> 17:44.228
BUT I DIDN'T
SAVE YOUR LIFE.

17:44.230 --> 17:46.564
IT TAKES A LOT MORE THAN THAT
TO SAVE A LIFE.

17:46.566 --> 17:48.166
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

17:48.168 --> 17:51.135
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU,
I'D BE STILL UP THERE,

17:51.137 --> 17:54.439
HANDING OUT CRULLERS TO MILLER,
MILLER, MILLER, AND SCHWARTZ.

17:54.441 --> 17:56.607
WELL, NOT SCHWARTZ.
HE'S GLUCOSE-INTOLERANT.

17:56.609 --> 17:58.476
[CHUCKLES]

17:58.478 --> 18:00.144
[KELLY]:
<i>"THE TRUTH IS, CHARLIE,</i>

18:00.146 --> 18:03.247
<i>"I DON'T KNOW</i>
<i>WHO SAVED WHOSE LIFE THAT DAY.</i>

18:03.249 --> 18:05.683
<i>YOU MAY HAVE SAVED MINE.</i>
<i>I WON'T KNOW FOR AWHILE--"</i>

18:05.685 --> 18:07.418
[OLIVER]: "...FOR AWHILE,
BUT I'LL ALWAYS CHERISH

18:07.420 --> 18:11.656
THE DAY YOU QUIT MILLER, MILLER,
MILLER, AND SCHWARTZ--"

18:13.292 --> 18:14.425
THERE YOU GO.

18:14.427 --> 18:16.461
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:16.463 --> 18:18.496
KEEP GOING.

18:18.498 --> 18:19.697
OH, THERE'S NO NEED.

18:19.699 --> 18:22.233
"MILLER, MILLER, MILLER,
AND SCHWARTZ." RITA?

18:22.235 --> 18:23.568
OH! MERGERS AND ACQUISITIONS.

18:23.570 --> 18:26.237
THE COLORADO BANK BUILDING.
9424 LINCOLN STREET.

18:26.239 --> 18:27.438
WE SEND THEIR
HUMAN RELATIONS OFFICE

18:27.440 --> 18:28.706
A FORM 407B,

18:28.708 --> 18:30.308
REQUESTING THE NAMES
OF TERMINATIONS

18:30.310 --> 18:31.542
ON JUNE 26TH OF LAST YEAR

18:31.544 --> 18:34.212
WITH THE FIRST NAME
"CHARLES" OR "CHARLIE."

18:34.214 --> 18:35.480
WHAT ABOUT KELLY?

18:35.482 --> 18:38.216
WHAT IS SHE DYING OF?
IS SHE GOING TO LIVE?

18:38.218 --> 18:39.550
READING ANY FURTHER
THAN NECESSARY

18:39.552 --> 18:41.519
VIOLATES THE PRIME DIRECTIVE.

18:41.521 --> 18:43.321
YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING!

18:43.323 --> 18:44.355
HE'S NOT KIDDING.

18:44.357 --> 18:46.357
WE DON'T KID.
WE'RE NOT KIDDERS.

18:47.493 --> 18:48.759
YOU KNOW DARN WELL
IT'LL TAKE WEEKS

18:48.761 --> 18:50.361
BEFORE SOME DRONE IN HR

18:50.363 --> 18:51.729
PULLS OUT A BUNCH OF
OLD EMPLOYMENT RECORDS

18:51.731 --> 18:53.564
TO HELP OUT
THE U.S. POST OFFICE.

18:53.566 --> 18:56.734
MEANWHILE,
CHARLIE IS OUT THERE SOMEWHERE,

18:56.736 --> 19:00.404
WONDERING WHY THE GIRL
OF HIS DREAMS BLEW HIM OFF

19:00.406 --> 19:01.606
WHEN THEY WERE SO OBVIOUSLY
FALLING IN LOVE.

19:01.608 --> 19:02.773
THERE IS
NOTHING IN HERE

19:02.775 --> 19:04.408
THAT INDICATES
THEY WERE IN LOVE.

19:04.410 --> 19:06.744
EVERYTHING
IN THAT LETTER SO FAR

19:06.746 --> 19:08.546
INDICATES THAT
THEY WERE FALLING IN LOVE!

19:08.548 --> 19:09.647
RIGHT, RITA?

19:09.649 --> 19:12.283
OH, I-I-I...

19:12.285 --> 19:15.686
I'VE NEVER ACTUALLY BEEN IN...

19:16.755 --> 19:18.556
NOT WHEN THE--

19:18.558 --> 19:22.460
NOT WHEN THE OTHER PERSON WAS
IN IT AT THE SAME TIME, SO...

19:22.462 --> 19:24.695
[NORMAN]:
I, UH, READ A BOOK ONCE

19:24.697 --> 19:26.831
ON CHEMICAL CHANGES
IN BABOONS,

19:26.833 --> 19:28.666
SUGGESTING
THAT APES EXPERIENCE

19:28.668 --> 19:31.435
CERTAIN EMOTIONAL CONNECTIONS
SIMILAR TO HUMAN LOVE.

19:33.272 --> 19:34.805
THANK YOU.

19:34.807 --> 19:36.641
WHY DON'T YOU
BRING THAT IN TOMORROW?

19:36.643 --> 19:38.509
[CLICKS PEN]

19:40.512 --> 19:41.512
OKAY.

19:41.514 --> 19:43.714
LOOK, IF-IF THERE'S A CHANCE

19:43.716 --> 19:46.584
THAT READING ONE MORE LINE
COULD GIVE US A TRULY SOLID SHOT

19:46.586 --> 19:49.520
AT REDIRECTING THAT LETTER
TO POOR CHARLIE, THEN...

19:49.522 --> 19:51.255
THEN DON'T WE OWE IT TO HIM?

19:51.257 --> 19:53.391
AND TO KELLY?

19:54.860 --> 19:57.428
I MEAN, "OF ALL THE ELEVATORS

19:57.430 --> 20:00.831
IN ALL THE TOWNS
IN ALL THE WORLD..."

20:00.833 --> 20:02.466
"WE?"

20:02.468 --> 20:05.603
YOU MEAN "US," MS. McINERNEY?

20:05.605 --> 20:07.471
OR COULD IT BE
THAT YOU'VE ALREADY TAKEN

20:07.473 --> 20:09.273
OUR LITTLE ENTERPRISE
INTO YOUR HEART?

20:09.275 --> 20:11.642
THAT'S VERY TOUCHING,
BUT THE ANSWER IS NO.

20:11.644 --> 20:13.778
[♪]

20:31.363 --> 20:32.663
AHEM.

20:35.634 --> 20:38.402
♪ ...WRITE A LETTER
FROM ME TO YOU ♪

20:38.404 --> 20:43.574
♪ TELLING ME WHAT YOU ARE DOING
THESE DAYS... ♪

20:45.444 --> 20:51.582
I'VE HEARD OF COP BARS
AND SPORTS BARS AND MAFIA BARS.

20:51.584 --> 20:53.551
NEVER BEEN TO A POSTAL BAR.

20:53.553 --> 20:54.785
EVERYONE
NEEDS A PLACE

20:54.787 --> 20:56.487
TO DECOMPRESS
WITH THEIR PEERS.

20:56.489 --> 21:00.391
ACTUALLY, UH,
THESE ARE NOT MY PEERS,

21:00.393 --> 21:02.293
BUT THEY ARE CLEARLY YOURS,

21:02.295 --> 21:03.694
AND I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
ENJOY IT HERE.

21:03.696 --> 21:05.596
AREN'T YOU A CHARMER?

21:05.598 --> 21:06.831
HEY, SHANE!

21:06.833 --> 21:10.835
HEY, YOU SPELL McINERNEY
WITH AN M-C, RIGHT?

21:10.837 --> 21:12.303
UH, YEAH.

21:12.305 --> 21:13.471
OHH!

21:13.473 --> 21:15.506
EXCELLENT.
I HAVE A SURPRISE FOR YOU.

21:15.508 --> 21:16.807
RITA IS

21:16.809 --> 21:19.677
A CONNOISSEUR OF
THE CAREFULLY-CRAFTED DAIQUIRI.

21:19.679 --> 21:22.747
BARKEEP, A GIN RICKEY, PLEASE?
HOLD THE RICKEY.

21:22.749 --> 21:25.416
MAKE THAT TWO.
OH! DO YOU HAVE WINGS?

21:27.786 --> 21:31.389
MILLER, MILLER, MILLER,
AND SCHWARTZ WERE SUED FOR FRAUD

21:31.391 --> 21:33.324
AND WENT OUT OF BUSINESS
SIX MONTHS AGO.

21:33.326 --> 21:35.626
WELL, SO MUCH
FOR OUR ONLY LEAD.

21:35.628 --> 21:39.363
YOU COULD'VE JUST LET ME LOOK
THIS CHARLIE GUY UP

21:39.365 --> 21:40.831
AND IT WOULD'VE TAKEN ME
30 SECONDS.

21:40.833 --> 21:42.900
THIS IS NOT A RACE
WE RUN, MS. McINERNEY.

21:42.902 --> 21:44.468
IT IS A JOURNEY.

21:44.470 --> 21:46.437
IT IS A JOB, OLIVER!

21:46.439 --> 21:47.571
YOU DELIVER ONE LETTER,

21:47.573 --> 21:48.806
AND THE NEXT DAY,

21:48.808 --> 21:50.541
THERE ARE A HUNDRED MORE
TO TAKE ITS PLACE.

21:50.543 --> 21:53.477
IT'S A LOSING BATTLE,
AN EXERCISE IN FUTILITY.

21:53.479 --> 21:55.980
IT'S NOT
SOME WOO-WOO SPIRITUAL JOURNEY.

21:55.982 --> 21:58.349
THERE ARE MORE THINGS
IN HEAVEN AND EARTH, HORATIO,

21:58.351 --> 22:00.785
THAN ARE DREAMT OF
IN YOUR PHILOSOPHY.

22:00.787 --> 22:01.852
IT'S NOT HORATIO,
IT'S SHERYL.

22:01.854 --> 22:03.587
IT'S SHANE!

22:03.589 --> 22:05.723
IT'S SHAKESPEARE,
PEASANTS.

22:05.725 --> 22:08.492
YOU MAY LACK
A SENSE OF DESTINY,

22:08.494 --> 22:11.462
BUT YOU HAVE ONE CHARACTERISTIC
THAT, IF CAREFULLY CULTIVATED,

22:11.464 --> 22:12.930
COULD BE HELPFUL.

22:12.932 --> 22:15.800
IT'S SOMETHING
I LIKE TO CALL CURIOSITY.

22:15.802 --> 22:16.867
MM.

22:16.869 --> 22:19.670
YOU WANTED TO KNOW
WHY WE'RE HERE?

22:22.607 --> 22:24.909
[♪]

22:26.745 --> 22:29.914
I CAN EXPLAIN.

22:29.916 --> 22:31.949
OKAY, I CAN'T EXPLAIN,

22:31.951 --> 22:34.652
BUT I CAN TELL YOU
THAT I DIDN'T READ IT,

22:34.654 --> 22:35.786
SO, TECHNICALLY...

22:35.788 --> 22:36.987
UNAUTHORIZED REMOVAL

22:36.989 --> 22:39.490
IS A GROSS VIOLATION
OF REGULATION 67K.

22:39.492 --> 22:41.092
YES, IT IS.

22:43.628 --> 22:46.964
BUT IN THIS CASE...
A CONVENIENT ONE.

22:47.966 --> 22:49.867
WHAT?

22:58.844 --> 23:01.979
I THOUGHT YOU NEVER
BROKE THE RULES.

23:01.981 --> 23:04.548
APPARENTLY, WE HAVE YOU
TO DO THAT FOR US.

23:04.550 --> 23:05.816
I, HOWEVER,

23:05.818 --> 23:07.718
ON OCCASION,
MUST BEND THE LAW

23:07.720 --> 23:10.054
IN ORDER TO FULFILL
THE SPIRIT OF THE LAW.

23:10.056 --> 23:12.723
NORMAN, PLEASE RETRIEVE RITA.
SHE WON'T WANT TO MISS THIS.

23:13.792 --> 23:15.593
NUTS?

23:19.898 --> 23:21.565
THANK YOU.

23:21.567 --> 23:23.000
FOR WHAT?

23:23.002 --> 23:25.536
FOR OUTING ME HERE
AND NOT BACK AT THE OFFICE,

23:25.538 --> 23:26.804
IN FRONT OF ANDREA.

23:26.806 --> 23:28.672
I PREFER TO DO
AS LITTLE AS POSSIBLE

23:28.674 --> 23:30.474
IN FRONT OF ANDREA.

23:30.476 --> 23:32.643
[♪]

23:34.045 --> 23:35.646
WELCOME, RITA.

23:35.648 --> 23:38.516
I ASSUME YOU REMEMBER
WHERE WE LEFT OFF?

23:38.518 --> 23:39.750
[RITA SIGHS WISTFULLY]

23:39.752 --> 23:41.819
"I'LL ALWAYS CHERISH
THE MEMORY OF--"

23:41.821 --> 23:42.887
-OH, HERE IT IS.
-"...THAT DAY--"

23:42.889 --> 23:44.054
"...WHEN WE MET

23:44.056 --> 23:46.624
AND TRIED SO HARD
NOT TO FALL IN LOVE."

23:48.693 --> 23:50.795
THERE'S AN ART
TO THE PERFECT

23:50.797 --> 23:51.796
BAGEL AND LOX COMBO.

23:51.798 --> 23:52.997
OKAY.

23:52.999 --> 23:54.598
YOU GOT YOUR ONIONS,
TOMATOES, CREAM CHEESE,

23:54.600 --> 23:56.033
ALL YOUR
MAJOR FOOD GROUPS.

23:56.035 --> 23:57.902
YOU EAT ONE OF THESE,
YOU'RE GOOD FOR THE DAY?

23:57.904 --> 23:59.003
OH, YEAH.

23:59.005 --> 24:00.704
AND THESE ARE...?

24:00.706 --> 24:03.040
AH. CAPERS. THE KEY
TO THE WHOLE ENTERPRISE.

24:03.042 --> 24:04.608
AH! UH-OH.

24:04.610 --> 24:05.776
THE SECRET IS,

24:05.778 --> 24:06.977
YOU SORT OF...

24:06.979 --> 24:11.081
GLUE THE CAPER
INTO THE CHEESE,

24:11.083 --> 24:13.851
THAT WAY,
THEY DON'T ROLL OFF.

24:13.853 --> 24:15.753
AND THEN THE SALMON,

24:15.755 --> 24:17.755
THEN THE TOMATO...

24:17.757 --> 24:20.591
AND THE ONION.

24:20.593 --> 24:21.892
AND...

24:27.566 --> 24:30.000
[♪]

24:30.002 --> 24:33.070
YOU'VE--
YOU'VE GOT SOME...

24:33.072 --> 24:35.806
RIGHT...

24:35.808 --> 24:37.608
THERE.

24:37.610 --> 24:39.877
[CHARLIE CHUCKLES]

24:39.879 --> 24:41.612
GREAT NOSE, BY THE WAY.

24:41.614 --> 24:43.547
PEOPLE PROBABLY
TELL YOU THAT A LOT, RIGHT?

24:43.549 --> 24:45.015
YOUR BOYFRIEND, PROBABLY.

24:45.017 --> 24:46.750
YOU KNOW, FORGET THAT.

24:46.752 --> 24:49.053
THAT'S-- THAT'S TOO MUCH
INFORMATION FOR A FIRST DATE.

24:49.055 --> 24:53.057
THIS IS A... DATE, RIGHT?

24:53.059 --> 24:54.124
SORT OF?

24:57.863 --> 24:59.864
I HAVE A PROPOSITION.

24:59.866 --> 25:00.898
YES.

25:00.900 --> 25:02.766
WHATEVER IT IS...

25:02.768 --> 25:04.235
YES.

25:07.873 --> 25:09.773
SO, NO LAST NAMES?

25:09.775 --> 25:11.141
RIGHT.

25:11.143 --> 25:14.578
NO EMAILS, NO PHONE NUMBERS,
NO TEXTING?

25:14.580 --> 25:15.646
NO TWEETS.

25:15.648 --> 25:16.981
WE JUST SPEND
ONE DAY TOGETHER,

25:16.983 --> 25:18.549
SAY WHATEVER
WE WANT TO SAY

25:18.551 --> 25:19.884
WITH NO FEAR,
NO JUDGMENT,

25:19.886 --> 25:22.052
BECAUSE WE WON'T
SEE EACH OTHER AGAIN.

25:22.054 --> 25:23.587
YEAH, SEE,

25:23.589 --> 25:24.989
THAT'S THE PART
I'M HAVING TROUBLE WITH.

25:24.991 --> 25:25.990
WELL, THINK ABOUT IT.

25:25.992 --> 25:27.091
I MEAN, ONE DAY

25:27.093 --> 25:28.659
WHEN YOU DON'T
HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT

25:28.661 --> 25:30.127
WHAT YOU DO OR SAY
WILL AFFECT TOMORROW.

25:30.129 --> 25:31.795
WE'RE JUST LIVING...

25:31.797 --> 25:32.897
RIGHT NOW,

25:32.899 --> 25:34.198
TODAY.

25:34.200 --> 25:36.901
IS THIS PART OF
YOUR "LIFE IS SHORT" PHILOSOPHY?

25:37.869 --> 25:39.737
ARE YOU IN OR OUT?

25:41.806 --> 25:45.109
NO TEXTING, NO TWEETING...
A GIRL AFTER MY OWN HEART.

25:45.111 --> 25:48.612
WHAT ABOUT CHARLIE?
IS HE IN OR IS HE OUT?

25:48.614 --> 25:50.681
WELL, FROM THE LENGTH
OF THIS LETTER,

25:50.683 --> 25:53.050
I ASSUME HE BOUGHT INTO
THE UNORTHODOX PLAN,

25:53.052 --> 25:54.919
BUT IF THE LAST PAGES
YIELD AS FEW CLUES

25:54.921 --> 25:56.220
AS THE FIRST PAGES,

25:56.222 --> 25:57.955
WE'RE GONNA BE HARD-PRESSED
TO FIND THE WRITER.

25:57.957 --> 25:59.723
OR THE WRITEE.

25:59.725 --> 26:00.991
I'VE GOT AN IDEA.

26:00.993 --> 26:02.860
OH, HAPPY DAY.

26:02.862 --> 26:04.094
IN THE LETTER,

26:04.096 --> 26:05.696
IT SAYS THAT THEY WENT TO A PARK
TOGETHER, RIGHT?

26:05.698 --> 26:07.164
"KELLY, FROM WASHINGTON PARK."
YEAH.

26:07.166 --> 26:08.599
I HAVE A PROPOSITION.

26:08.601 --> 26:10.601
NO.

26:10.603 --> 26:12.603
WHATEVER IT IS, NO.

26:12.605 --> 26:14.138
SHE USED A BICYCLE STAMP,

26:14.140 --> 26:16.607
AND YOU SAID THAT
SHE WAS SENTIMENTAL, RIGHT?

26:16.609 --> 26:19.009
I BET THEY WENT TO THAT PARK
AND RENTED BIKES

26:19.011 --> 26:20.110
FROM RITA'S LITTLE OLD MAN.

26:20.112 --> 26:21.679
-SCHWINNS.
-SCHWINNS!

26:21.681 --> 26:22.947
OH! SCHWINNS.

26:22.949 --> 26:25.115
I PROPOSE...

26:25.117 --> 26:27.117
WE GO TO THE PARK TOMORROW,

26:27.119 --> 26:29.753
ON OUR LUNCH BREAK,
AND TALK TO HIM.

26:29.755 --> 26:31.021
THIS IS...

26:31.023 --> 26:32.856
HIGHLY IRREGULAR.

26:32.858 --> 26:34.158
WE'RE LOOKING FOR CLUES
IN A LOVE LETTER

26:34.160 --> 26:35.859
THAT AREN'T ALL GOING TO
BE IN THE LETTER.

26:35.861 --> 26:38.095
YEAH, AND SOME OF US COULD
REALLY USE SOME FRESH AIR.

26:38.097 --> 26:39.797
YEAH, OLIVER!

26:43.635 --> 26:46.804
ARE YOU IN OR ARE YOU OUT?

26:59.985 --> 27:02.152
[SIGHS]: OH. OH, NO.

27:02.154 --> 27:04.688
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

27:04.690 --> 27:07.257
HE USED TO SIT RIGHT HERE
AND NOW HE'S BEEN REPLACED BY...

27:07.259 --> 27:09.059
BY THIS.

27:09.061 --> 27:13.263
ANOTHER DREADFUL EXAMPLE
OF UNNECESSARY AUTOMATION.

27:13.265 --> 27:14.665
WELL, SHALL WE CONTINUE?

27:14.667 --> 27:15.799
READ ON, MacDUFF.

27:15.801 --> 27:19.003
SHAKESPEARE.

27:19.005 --> 27:20.704
"I KNOW I GAVE YOU
A PRETTY CRAZY REASON

27:20.706 --> 27:23.140
FOR ONLY SPENDING
ONE DAY TOGETHER, CHARLIE--"

27:23.142 --> 27:25.175
[KELLY]: <i>"BUT THE TRUTH IS,</i>
<i>I ONLY HAD ONE DAY TO SPEND.</i>

27:25.177 --> 27:29.079
<i>BUT SPENDING IT WITH YOU</i>
<i>MADE ALL THE DIFFERENCE."</i>

27:29.081 --> 27:31.915
[♪]

27:31.917 --> 27:34.785
♪ THIS SONG'S FOR YOU

27:34.787 --> 27:38.722
♪ IF WE COME TO A CLOSE

27:38.724 --> 27:44.928
♪ AND KEEP IT SOMEWHERE
DEEP INSIDE YOUR SOUL ♪

27:44.930 --> 27:52.069
♪ IT'S TRUE, WE MET
IN SUCH TURBULENT TIMES ♪

27:52.071 --> 27:55.806
♪ BUT I WANT YOU TO KNOW
YOU'RE THE BRIGHTEST STAR ♪

27:55.808 --> 27:59.109
♪ I'VE SEEN IN THE SKY

27:59.111 --> 28:01.178
OH! I WASN'T DONE YET.

28:01.180 --> 28:08.152
♪ THIS SONG'S FOR YOU
WHEN YOU'RE FEELING DOWN ♪

28:08.154 --> 28:13.824
♪ LET THE WORDS
PUT YOUR FEET ON THE GROUND ♪

28:13.826 --> 28:16.160
[CHATTING HAPPILY]

28:16.162 --> 28:20.764
♪ REMEMBER ME
AS A WARM JULY ♪

28:20.766 --> 28:22.232
♪ AND I'LL LOOK FOR YOU

28:22.234 --> 28:27.971
♪ AS THE BIGGEST
BLUE-EYED STAR IN THE SKY ♪

28:29.074 --> 28:31.241
WHEN I WAS
IN SIXTH GRADE,

28:31.243 --> 28:33.277
I USED TO CROSS
THIS BRIDGE EVERY DAY

28:33.279 --> 28:34.878
ON THE WAY TO SCHOOL.

28:34.880 --> 28:36.814
HEY, CAREFUL.
NO HISTORICAL DETAILS.

28:36.816 --> 28:38.348
I KNOW, I KNOW.

28:38.350 --> 28:40.818
BUT YOU SEE THIS CREEK?

28:40.820 --> 28:42.286
ALL THE KIDS
WOULD SWING ACROSS

28:42.288 --> 28:44.154
ON THAT ROPE

28:44.156 --> 28:45.756
INSTEAD OF
TAKING THE BRIDGE.

28:45.758 --> 28:47.091
BUT YOU TOOK
THE BRIDGE?

28:47.093 --> 28:50.127
I TRIED TO
SWING ACROSS AT FIRST.

28:50.129 --> 28:51.762
I'D GRAB THE ROPE, BUT...

28:51.764 --> 28:53.263
SOMETHING ALWAYS MADE ME
PUT ON THE BRAKES

28:53.265 --> 28:54.364
AT THE LAST SECOND.

28:54.366 --> 28:57.267
GOD, IT WAS EMBARRASSING.

28:57.269 --> 28:59.002
ALL THE KIDS WOULD BE
ON THE OTHER SIDE,

28:59.004 --> 29:01.271
YELLING, "COME ON, CHARLIE!
YOU CAN DO IT."

29:01.273 --> 29:03.407
BUT?

29:03.409 --> 29:05.976
BUT I NEVER DID.

29:05.978 --> 29:09.980
AFTER AWHILE, THEY STOPPED
EXPECTING ME TO EVEN TRY.

29:13.151 --> 29:14.852
SO DO IT TODAY.

29:14.854 --> 29:16.253
WHAT?

29:16.255 --> 29:18.222
SWING! WHAT
ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

29:18.224 --> 29:20.157
DITCH YOUR PRIDE.

29:20.159 --> 29:21.892
OKAY.

29:21.894 --> 29:23.360
YOU WAIT HERE.

29:23.362 --> 29:25.129
AND DON'T DISTRACT ME.

29:25.131 --> 29:26.830
-ALRIGHT.
-AND NO CAMERAS.

29:26.832 --> 29:28.232
HEY, YOU MAY WANT A RECORD
OF THIS SOMEDAY.

29:28.234 --> 29:29.900
SOMEDAY?

29:29.902 --> 29:31.301
NOW, IF THERE'S A CHANCE
WE COULD HAVE A "SOMEDAY,"

29:31.303 --> 29:33.137
THAT'S WORTH
RISKING MY LIFE FOR.

29:33.139 --> 29:35.105
OR MY PRIDE.

29:52.123 --> 29:54.992
THREE! TWO! ONE...

29:56.094 --> 29:58.028
[ROARING]: AHH!

29:58.030 --> 29:59.897
WHOO!

29:59.899 --> 30:01.465
[LAUGHING VICTORIOUSLY]

30:01.467 --> 30:03.033
YES! WHOO!

30:03.035 --> 30:04.201
-YEAH!
-OOF!

30:04.203 --> 30:05.936
-[BOTH GASPING]
-[THUDDING]

30:05.938 --> 30:08.272
-ARE YOU ALRIGHT?
-YEAH, I'M GOOD.

30:08.274 --> 30:10.107
SORRY!

30:10.109 --> 30:11.275
[RESUMES LAUGHING]

30:11.277 --> 30:12.409
YES!

30:12.411 --> 30:15.045
WHOO! THAT WAS AMAZING!

30:15.047 --> 30:17.080
-ARE YOU OKAY?
-DID YOU SEE THAT? YEAH!

30:17.082 --> 30:19.183
PRIDE GOETH BEFORE
A FALL, I GUESS.

30:19.185 --> 30:21.018
YOU LOST
A BUTTON, THOUGH.

30:21.020 --> 30:22.119
A SMALL SACRIFICE

30:22.121 --> 30:23.954
FOR THE LEAP
OF A LIFETIME.

30:23.956 --> 30:25.189
WELL, YOU WERE AWFULLY NICE
TO THAT GUY,

30:25.191 --> 30:26.456
CONSIDERING
HE KNOCKED YOU DOWN.

30:26.458 --> 30:29.993
WELL, LIFE IS SHORT.

30:29.995 --> 30:31.228
THAT WAS SO FUN!

30:31.230 --> 30:33.931
[CONTENTED SIGH]
AH! WHOO!

30:36.267 --> 30:38.936
[KELLY, WRITING]:
<i>"I THINK THAT WAS THE MOMENT</i>

30:38.938 --> 30:41.171
<i>"I REALIZED</i>
<i>HOW MUCH I WANTED TO LIVE.</i>

30:41.173 --> 30:44.441
<i>"HOW MUCH I NEEDED TO BELIEVE</i>
<i>IN A "SOMEDAY" WITH YOU IN IT.</i>

30:44.443 --> 30:47.945
<i>"MAYBE THAT'S HOW IT FEELS</i>
<i>TO FALL IN LOVE, CHARLIE--</i>

30:47.947 --> 30:51.114
<i>WHEN YOU CAN'T WAIT</i>
<i>FOR TOMORROW."</i>

30:51.116 --> 30:53.183
I JUST WANT TO TAKE
A COUPLE OF PICTURES.

30:53.185 --> 30:54.384
IT'S SO PRETTY HERE.

30:54.386 --> 30:55.519
GO FOR IT.

30:59.490 --> 31:02.226
[♪]

31:14.372 --> 31:17.507
SO, AM I EVER GONNA
SEE ANY OF THESE PICTURES?

31:18.910 --> 31:21.078
I MEAN, IF WE'RE NOT GONNA
SEE EACH OTHER AGAIN,

31:21.080 --> 31:22.346
YOU COULD AT LEAST

31:22.348 --> 31:24.982
UPLOAD THEM TO
THE CHARLIE-AND-KELLY WEBSITE.

31:24.984 --> 31:28.352
OH, NOW YOU WANT ME
TO BREAK THE RULES?

31:29.287 --> 31:31.021
WHY DO YOU
LIKE TAKING PICTURES?

31:32.423 --> 31:34.358
UH, LET ME SEE.

31:34.360 --> 31:35.292
WELL, UM...

31:35.294 --> 31:37.027
I KNOW, IN SOME CULTURES,

31:37.029 --> 31:39.129
PEOPLE THINK TAKING
A PHOTOGRAPH OF SOMETHING

31:39.131 --> 31:41.231
IS LIKE STEALING
A PIECE OF ITS SOUL.

31:41.233 --> 31:43.000
BUT FOR ME,

31:43.002 --> 31:48.105
TAKING A PICTURE OF SOMEONE
OR SOMETHING IS A WAY TO...

31:48.107 --> 31:50.007
I DON'T KNOW...
TO HONOR A SOUL.

31:50.009 --> 31:52.309
IT'S MY WAY
OF SAYING,

31:52.311 --> 31:54.111
"HERE YOU ARE, TREE...

31:54.113 --> 31:56.446
"HERE YOU ARE, SKY...

31:56.448 --> 31:59.082
HERE YOU ARE, CHARLIE."

31:59.084 --> 32:03.453
AND...
FOR JUST A MOMENT

32:03.455 --> 32:07.124
I GET TO STOP TIME
AND REALLY SEE YOU.

32:14.098 --> 32:16.233
[SHUTTER SNAPS]

32:17.235 --> 32:19.303
[CHUCKLES]

32:23.241 --> 32:25.409
WHAT?
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

32:28.479 --> 32:30.614
I'M JUST READING
THIS ARTICLE HERE

32:30.616 --> 32:34.418
ABOUT "ROGER PIPERSON, AGE 61,"

32:34.420 --> 32:38.188
A BAKER
WHO WON THE LOTTERY LAST WEEK.

32:38.190 --> 32:39.623
I BET EVERYBODY THINKS

32:39.625 --> 32:41.558
HE'S THE LUCKIEST GUY
IN THE WORLD.

32:41.560 --> 32:43.560
AND YESTERDAY,
I WOULD HAVE, TOO.

32:43.562 --> 32:45.195
BUT TODAY,

32:45.197 --> 32:48.265
I THINK
THE LUCKIEST GUY IN THE WORLD

32:48.267 --> 32:50.200
IS ME.

32:56.574 --> 32:58.175
CLICK.

32:58.177 --> 33:00.010
[NORMAN]: UH, ON
THE OTHER SIDE OF THIS PARK,

33:00.012 --> 33:01.611
THERE IS AN EXACT REPLICA
OF MARTHA WASHINGTON'S GARDEN

33:01.613 --> 33:03.447
AT MOUNT VERNON, VIRGINIA.

33:03.449 --> 33:05.048
I'M A DIRECT DESCENDANT

33:05.050 --> 33:07.584
OF GEORGE WASHINGTON'S
ACCOUNTANT.

33:09.020 --> 33:12.322
I DON'T SEE THE PURPOSE
IN CONTINUING THIS FIELD TRIP.

33:12.324 --> 33:14.558
JUST A LITTLE BIT LONGER,
OLIVER, PLEASE?

33:14.560 --> 33:16.560
JUST READ A LITTLE BIT MORE.

33:16.562 --> 33:18.228
THERE'S GOT TO BE SOMETHING
IN THAT LETTER

33:18.230 --> 33:19.428
THAT WILL HELP US

33:19.430 --> 33:21.264
IF WE PUT OURSELVES
IN CHARLIE AND KELLY'S PLACE.

33:21.266 --> 33:23.066
I AM NOT GOING TO SWING
ACROSS THE CREEK.

33:23.068 --> 33:24.501
FINE.

33:24.503 --> 33:27.404
AND TOMORROW,
EVERYTHING GOES BACK TO NORMAL.

33:27.406 --> 33:30.674
MM-HMM. IF THAT'S
WHAT YOU CONSIDER NORMAL.

33:32.176 --> 33:33.410
[SIGHS]

33:33.412 --> 33:35.379
"I WANTED
TO TELL YOU EVERYTHING

33:35.381 --> 33:36.579
RIGHT THEN, CHARLIE--"

33:36.581 --> 33:39.316
<i>...BUT I DIDN'T WANT</i>
<i>TO BREAK THE SPELL."</i>

33:39.318 --> 33:41.218
[KELLY]:
"I'VE ALWAYS BEEN GOOD AT

33:41.220 --> 33:42.185
PUTTING OFF THE HARD STUFF."

33:42.187 --> 33:43.286
[SHUTTER SNAPS]

33:44.555 --> 33:47.557
I THINK WE OUGHT
TO DO SOMETHING.

33:47.559 --> 33:49.226
SOMETHING
TO COMMEMORATE THIS DAY.

33:49.228 --> 33:51.328
SOMETHING
THAT MAKES A DIFFERENCE.

33:51.330 --> 33:52.629
WE COULD GET MARRIED.

33:52.631 --> 33:55.432
TEMPTING, BUT I DON'T MARRY
ON THE FIRST DATE.

33:55.434 --> 33:57.300
GOOD POINT.

33:57.302 --> 33:58.602
ALRIGHT. UH...

33:58.604 --> 34:00.337
LET'S SEE.

34:00.339 --> 34:02.139
I GOT IT!

34:02.141 --> 34:03.440
YOU SAVED
MY LIFE TODAY.

34:03.442 --> 34:05.642
LET'S SAVE
SOME MORE.

34:06.611 --> 34:08.211
[KELLY]:
YOU WANT TO GIVE BLOOD?

34:08.213 --> 34:10.680
YEAH. THEY GIVE YOU COOKIES,

34:10.682 --> 34:13.183
AND YOU GET TO LIE DOWN,
AND IT'S FREE.

34:13.185 --> 34:15.485
I DON'T REALLY
GIVE BLOOD ANYMORE, SO.

34:15.487 --> 34:18.088
COME ON! THEY DO IT
ONCE A YEAR HERE IN THE PARK

34:18.090 --> 34:19.388
AND IT MAKES YOU FEEL GREAT.

34:19.390 --> 34:21.658
YOU WON'T SWING ACROSS A CREEK,
BUT NEEDLES ARE NO PROBLEM?

34:21.660 --> 34:23.193
I KNOW. GO FIGURE.

34:23.195 --> 34:24.528
I USED TO DO IT
ALL THE TIME IN COLLEGE.

34:24.530 --> 34:27.631
I THINK I STILL HAVE
MY OLD DONOR CARD...

34:27.633 --> 34:29.599
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

34:29.601 --> 34:32.569
OH, MAN.
I THINK I, UH...

34:32.571 --> 34:35.539
I THINK
I LOST MY WALLET.

34:35.541 --> 34:37.641
[KELLY SIGHS]

34:37.643 --> 34:41.411
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU LOST
YOUR JOB AND YOUR WALLET

34:41.413 --> 34:43.480
ON THE SAME DAY.

34:43.482 --> 34:45.482
FOUND YOUR BUTTON, THOUGH.

34:45.484 --> 34:48.385
TO BE ACCURATE,
I QUIT MY JOB.

34:48.387 --> 34:50.620
I DID LOSE MY WALLET,

34:50.622 --> 34:52.756
BUT I FOUND
THE GIRL OF MY DREAMS,

34:52.758 --> 34:55.525
SO I THINK
IT ALL BALANCES OUT.

34:57.128 --> 34:58.395
EXCEPT...

34:58.397 --> 35:00.530
WHEN I WAKE UP
TOMORROW MORNING

35:00.532 --> 35:02.699
AND REALIZE
THAT I LOST THE GIRL.

35:08.473 --> 35:10.640
I'M SORRY, CHARLIE,
IT JUST...

35:10.642 --> 35:13.543
IT HAS TO BE THIS WAY.

35:14.679 --> 35:16.346
PROMISE ME...

35:16.348 --> 35:19.249
YOU'LL GO HOME TONIGHT,

35:19.251 --> 35:21.518
AND YOU'LL SEW THIS BUTTON
BACK ON YOUR BLAZER

35:21.520 --> 35:24.187
AND YOU'LL FIND YOURSELF
THE JOB OF YOUR DREAMS

35:24.189 --> 35:27.190
AND YOU'LL MEET
SOMEBODY WONDERFUL

35:27.192 --> 35:30.193
AND HAVE LOTS OF BABIES
AND GRANDCHILDREN,

35:30.195 --> 35:32.696
AND MAKE DOZENS OF PAPER BOATS
FOR THEM

35:32.698 --> 35:35.398
EVERY TIME YOU TAKE THEM
FOR WALKS IN THE PARK,

35:35.400 --> 35:38.435
AND WHEN YOU SET THEM SAILING,

35:38.437 --> 35:40.704
YOU'LL THINK OF ME.

35:48.179 --> 35:52.616
OR YOU COULD COME BY TOMORROW
AND SEW THE BUTTON ON YOURSELF.

35:53.551 --> 35:54.751
[CHUCKLES SADLY]

35:54.753 --> 35:57.687
ARE YOU TRYING TO TELL ME
YOU CAN'T SEW?

35:57.689 --> 36:00.790
I DON'T THINK I COULD DO
ANYTHING WITHOUT YOU NOW, KELLY.

36:05.596 --> 36:08.532
[♪]

36:15.339 --> 36:17.507
ONE MORE THING.

36:17.509 --> 36:20.377
OKAY?
JUST ONE MORE.

36:22.280 --> 36:23.813
IF YOU SWING
REALLY HIGH...

36:23.815 --> 36:26.550
OVER THE TREES...

36:26.552 --> 36:29.386
YOU SEE THE BIG
APARTMENT BUILDING?

36:29.388 --> 36:30.453
I SEE IT.

36:30.455 --> 36:32.489
OKAY, NOW
LOOK TO THE RIGHT.

36:32.491 --> 36:34.591
YOU SEE THE ROOFTOPS?

36:34.593 --> 36:36.593
YOU SEE 'EM?

36:36.595 --> 36:38.495
-YEP!
-OKAY.

36:38.497 --> 36:43.233
NOW LOOK FOR A BLUE GATE
WITH A FLAG ABOVE IT.

36:43.235 --> 36:45.535
YES! THERE IT IS. I SAW IT.

36:45.537 --> 36:47.637
THAT'S ME. THE BLUE GATE.

36:47.639 --> 36:48.872
THAT'S WHERE I LIVE.

36:48.874 --> 36:50.874
CHAR...
YOU'RE BREAKING THE RULE!

36:50.876 --> 36:52.576
YEAH, WELL, YOU'RE
BREAKING MY HEART.

36:52.578 --> 36:54.744
COME ON, PROMISE ME
THAT TOMORROW MORNING

36:54.746 --> 36:57.347
I'M GONNA WAKE UP, AND YOU'LL
BE SITTING ON MY FRONT STEPS.

36:57.349 --> 36:58.748
CHARLIE, I--

36:58.750 --> 37:00.650
YOU'RE NOT COMIN' DOWN
UNTIL YOU DO!

37:00.652 --> 37:02.352
[KELLY YELPS AND LAUGHS]

37:02.354 --> 37:04.421
HIGHER!

37:09.327 --> 37:10.694
THERE IT IS!

37:10.696 --> 37:11.728
WHAT? THE BLUE GATE?

37:11.730 --> 37:13.463
YEAH!

37:13.465 --> 37:16.333
THE BLUE GATE.

37:18.369 --> 37:19.369
LET'S GO.

37:19.371 --> 37:20.370
WAIT!

37:20.372 --> 37:21.838
DID KELLY GO?

37:21.840 --> 37:24.507
DID SHE SHOW UP TOMORROW...
LAST YEAR?

37:24.509 --> 37:26.810
IT'S NOT UP TO US
TO DECIDE WHAT--

37:26.812 --> 37:28.478
[SIGHS]

37:28.480 --> 37:30.614
"AND THEN EVEN THOUGH
I WANTED TO COME BACK

37:30.616 --> 37:31.881
"AND FIND YOU THERE,

37:31.883 --> 37:34.284
"WAITING FOR ME ON THE STEPS
BY THE BLUE GATE,

37:34.286 --> 37:35.352
I COULDN'T."

37:35.354 --> 37:37.387
OHH. THAT'S
VERY DISAPPOINTING.

37:37.389 --> 37:38.788
"BUT I CAN EXPLAIN.

37:38.790 --> 37:41.625
"WITH ALL MY TALK ABOUT COURAGE,

37:41.627 --> 37:44.494
"YOU WERE THE ONE
WHO TOOK THE BIG LEAP YESTERDAY

37:44.496 --> 37:45.862
"AND NOW IT'S MY TURN.

37:45.864 --> 37:48.298
"I'M GOING TO DO WHAT
I HAVE TO DO TO GET MYSELF WELL.

37:48.300 --> 37:49.532
"IF IT WORKS,

37:49.534 --> 37:52.902
"LET'S MEET A YEAR FROM TODAY,

37:52.904 --> 37:54.404
"ON THE 26TH,

37:54.406 --> 37:55.804
"AND WE'LL GO ON A SECOND DATE.

37:55.906 --> 37:58.842
"BUT IF I'M NOT THERE
WAITING FOR YOU AT THE BRIDGE

37:58.844 --> 38:00.577
"AT 6:00,

38:00.579 --> 38:03.346
"YOU'LL KNOW IT'S ONLY BECAUSE
THE LEAP I HAD TO MAKE

38:03.348 --> 38:04.848
"WAS JUST TOO FAR.

38:04.850 --> 38:06.683
"WHATEVER HAPPENS, CHARLIE,

38:06.685 --> 38:09.686
"SEW THIS BUTTON ON
AND GO OUT INTO THE WORLD.

38:09.688 --> 38:12.689
"AND IF YOU EVER WANT TO SPEND
THAT DAY WITH ME AGAIN,

38:12.691 --> 38:15.558
"JUST REMEMBER HOW IT STARTED.

38:15.560 --> 38:17.794
"JUST REMEMBER--
LIFE IS SHORT.

38:18.963 --> 38:21.698
LOVE, KELLY."

38:21.700 --> 38:23.633
OH, MAN! WHAT'S TODAY?

38:23.635 --> 38:26.803
THE 23rd.
OH, WOW...

38:26.805 --> 38:29.472
CHARLIE HAS NO IDEA THEY'RE
SUPPOSED TO MEET IN THREE DAYS.

38:29.474 --> 38:31.541
THAT'S ASSUMING
SHE TOOK THE LEAP...

38:31.543 --> 38:34.544
MADE IT TO THE OTHER SIDE.

38:41.819 --> 38:43.953
[♪]

38:50.795 --> 38:53.363
WELL, I DON'T SEE
ANOTHER HOUSE ON THIS BLOCK

38:53.365 --> 38:55.765
WITH A BLUE GATE
AND A FLAG.

38:55.767 --> 38:57.000
WHO'S GONNA KNOCK?

38:57.002 --> 38:58.601
THERE WILL BE
NO KNOCKING.

38:58.603 --> 39:01.004
WE HAVE
THE ADDRESS NOW,

39:01.006 --> 39:02.872
SO WE GO BACK
TO THE OFFICE,

39:02.874 --> 39:03.940
FOLLOW PROCEDURE,

39:03.942 --> 39:05.475
BEFORE WE GET
INTO TROUBLE.

39:05.477 --> 39:07.510
SERIOUSLY, WE'RE HERE,
LET'S JUST GO AND--

39:07.512 --> 39:09.479
THAT'S UNACCEPTABLE,
MS. McINERNEY.

39:09.481 --> 39:11.915
BESIDES, I THOUGHT
YOU WOULD WELCOME

39:11.917 --> 39:13.483
THE OPPORTUNITY TO SHOW US

39:13.485 --> 39:15.485
WHAT THAT FANCY LAPTOP
OF YOURS CAN DO.

39:15.487 --> 39:17.587
[♪]

39:28.666 --> 39:29.833
[KEYS CLACKING]

39:29.835 --> 39:32.402
[SHANE]: HERE'S THE DOOR...

39:32.404 --> 39:33.603
[NORMAN]:
AH! THERE'S THE BLUE GATE.

39:33.605 --> 39:34.904
COOL!

39:34.906 --> 39:36.973
LAST-KNOWN OCCUPANT
CHARLES...

39:36.975 --> 39:39.876
-CHARLIE RIGGS.
-CHARLIE.

39:39.878 --> 39:41.044
[KEYS CLACKING]

39:41.046 --> 39:42.979
SO I GUESS WE CAN'T, UH,

39:42.981 --> 39:45.515
WRITE "GOOD LUCK"
ON THE BACK OF IT, HUH?

39:45.517 --> 39:47.917
WE RE-ADDRESS IT
AND RE-PACKAGE IT

39:47.919 --> 39:49.519
WITH A FORM EXPLAINING

39:49.521 --> 39:51.654
WHY THE LETTER WAS OPENED
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

39:51.656 --> 39:52.954
WAIT. YOU'RE GONNA MAIL IT?

39:52.956 --> 39:55.792
WE'VE PUSHED THE LIMITS
OF PROTOCOL ENOUGH ALREADY.

39:55.794 --> 39:58.828
NO, NO, NO. THEY ONLY
HAVE THREE DAYS!

39:58.830 --> 40:00.029
ARE YOU QUESTIONING

40:00.031 --> 40:01.598
THE EFFICIENCY
OF THIS FACILITY?

40:01.600 --> 40:02.932
WELL, IF THE ENVELOPE FITS!

40:02.934 --> 40:04.501
[OLIVER CHUCKLES]

40:04.503 --> 40:06.069
OKAY, WHAT IF,

40:06.071 --> 40:08.638
BY SOME INCOMPREHENSIBLE
TWIST OF FATE,

40:08.640 --> 40:10.774
IT TAKES THE U.S. POST OFFICE
MORE THAN THREE DAYS

40:10.776 --> 40:12.575
TO DELIVER
A SIMPLE LETTER?

40:12.577 --> 40:15.678
AND, IN THE MEANTIME,
KELLY SHOWS UP...

40:15.680 --> 40:18.548
AND SHE WAITS...

40:18.550 --> 40:20.750
AND WAITS...

40:20.752 --> 40:22.519
AND SHE WAITS,

40:22.521 --> 40:24.053
BUT HE NEVER COMES,

40:24.055 --> 40:26.756
AND SO SHE'S STANDING THERE,

40:26.758 --> 40:28.024
ON THE BRIDGE,

40:28.026 --> 40:29.659
ALONE,

40:29.661 --> 40:31.961
WONDERING HOW HE COULD
JUST LEAVE HER THERE,

40:31.963 --> 40:34.831
AFTER SHE SAID
SHE LOVES HIM SO MUCH?

40:34.833 --> 40:38.601
I ADMIRE YOUR PASSION,
MS. McINERNEY,

40:38.603 --> 40:41.037
BUT OUR JOB IS TO SIMPLY
REVIVE A DEAD LETTER

40:41.039 --> 40:42.572
AND SEND IT ALONG.

40:42.574 --> 40:44.040
AND, YES, THERE ARE TIMES

40:44.042 --> 40:46.576
WHEN WE WONDER WHAT WILL BECOME
OF THOSE WHO RECEIVE THEM,

40:46.578 --> 40:48.912
BUT WE ARE
THE UNITED STATES POST OFFICE.

40:48.914 --> 40:50.747
WE CANNOT PLAY GOD.

40:50.749 --> 40:53.650
YOU SAID YOU DON'T
BELIEVE IN COINCIDENCES.

40:53.652 --> 40:57.053
WHAT IF YOU HAD PULLED
A GREEN ENVELOPE OUT OF THERE,

40:57.055 --> 40:58.855
INSTEAD OF THAT PINK ONE?

40:58.857 --> 41:02.826
THEN CHARLIE AND KELLY WOULD
NEVER HAVE HAD A CHANCE.

41:02.828 --> 41:05.862
BUT NOW THEY DO.

41:05.864 --> 41:08.031
YOU'RE IMPECCABLE
AT YOUR JOB, OLIVER.

41:08.033 --> 41:11.601
BUT WHAT ABOUT YOUR JOB
AS A FELLOW HUMAN BEING

41:11.603 --> 41:15.672
WHO'S BEEN GIVEN THE OPPORTUNITY
TO CHANGE SOMEONE'S LIFE?

41:17.508 --> 41:20.743
WE MAY NEVER KNOW
THE WHOLE TRUTH ABOUT A LETTER

41:20.745 --> 41:22.745
OR WHAT HAPPENS TO IT
ONCE IT LEAVES US,

41:22.747 --> 41:23.947
MS. McINERNEY,

41:23.949 --> 41:25.682
BUT I BELIEVE ABSOLUTELY

41:25.684 --> 41:28.685
THAT WHAT WE DO HERE
DOES MAKES A DIFFERENCE.

41:28.687 --> 41:31.054
IT IS OUR RESPONSIBILITY

41:31.056 --> 41:33.022
TO GLEAN THE TRUTH
FROM A LOST LETTER,

41:33.024 --> 41:35.692
AND TOMORROW, BECAUSE
WE HAVE DONE OUR WORK WELL,

41:35.694 --> 41:37.760
THAT TRUTH WILL BE DELIVERED
TO MR. RIGGS--

41:37.762 --> 41:41.097
A YEAR LATE,
OR, HOPEFULLY, RIGHT ON TIME.

41:42.766 --> 41:45.168
BUT IT'S NOT UP TO US ANYMORE.

41:49.039 --> 41:50.773
[SHANE SIGHS]

41:50.775 --> 41:52.008
OLIVER...
OLIVER, PLEASE.

41:53.878 --> 41:56.012
[CHUTE WHOOSHING]

41:57.781 --> 42:00.617
[♪]

42:08.125 --> 42:10.560
NORMAN!

42:10.562 --> 42:12.095
WHERE'S OLIVER?

42:13.731 --> 42:15.865
UH, ON THE FLOOR.

42:15.867 --> 42:17.667
I WAS JUST ON THE FLOOR.
HE'S NOT THERE.

42:17.669 --> 42:20.737
ON THE FLOOR
SOMEWHERE ELSE MAYBE?

42:21.672 --> 42:24.240
GET THOSE PROCESSED BEFORE
THE DECADE'S OUT, WILL YA?

42:25.075 --> 42:26.075
HEY!

42:26.077 --> 42:27.644
FANCY-PANTS.

42:27.646 --> 42:29.178
THE TRANSFER
YOU PUT IN FOR?

42:29.180 --> 42:30.813
IT'S GONNA TAKE 10 WEEKS.

42:30.815 --> 42:32.916
10 WEEKS?

42:34.051 --> 42:36.619
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

42:36.621 --> 42:39.722
[FUMING GROAN]

42:39.724 --> 42:41.124
HEY! YOU REMEMBER

42:41.126 --> 42:43.159
THAT SURPRISE THAT
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT?

42:43.161 --> 42:44.827
THE LAST 24 HOURS

42:44.829 --> 42:47.096
HAVE BEEN NOTHING
BUT SURPRISES,

42:47.098 --> 42:48.765
BUT PLEASE, GO ON.

42:48.767 --> 42:49.866
WELL, I KNEW

42:49.868 --> 42:51.034
THAT I HAD SEEN
YOUR NAME SOMEWHERE,

42:51.036 --> 42:52.869
AND IT WAS ON A LETTER,
A DEAD LETTER

42:52.871 --> 42:54.103
THAT WAS ENTERED
INTO THE SYSTEM

42:54.105 --> 42:56.039
14 MONTHS AGO,
ON APRIL 28th,

42:56.041 --> 42:58.041
WHICH IS TWO DAYS
BEFORE YOUR BIRTHDAY.

42:58.043 --> 42:59.676
HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?

42:59.678 --> 43:01.044
BECAUSE I READ
YOUR FILE, REMEMBER?

43:02.780 --> 43:04.180
SO IT'S GOTTA BE
A BIRTHDAY CARD.

43:04.182 --> 43:05.915
WHERE IS IT?

43:05.917 --> 43:07.650
I MAILED IT TO YOU.

43:07.652 --> 43:09.652
YOU MAILED IT?
I WORK HERE.

43:09.654 --> 43:11.754
YOU COULD'VE JUST
HANDED IT TO ME.

43:11.756 --> 43:14.891
STANDARD PROCEDURE,
MS. McINERNEY.

43:14.893 --> 43:16.192
PROCEDURE? RIGHT.

43:16.194 --> 43:20.263
IT WAS MY BIRTHDAY
CARD FROM...

43:20.265 --> 43:21.664
WHO WAS IT FROM?

43:21.666 --> 43:23.132
OH. "RETURN
ADDRESS OBSCURED."

43:23.134 --> 43:25.001
SO WHERE
DID YOU MAIL IT?

43:25.003 --> 43:27.070
TO HERE.
CARE OF DEAD LETTERS.

43:27.072 --> 43:29.872
YOU PEOPLE ARE CRAZY.

43:29.874 --> 43:31.874
A POPULAR THEORY.
COFFEE?

43:31.876 --> 43:34.877
YOUR COFFEE IS SWILL

43:34.879 --> 43:36.746
AND I'M WASTING
MY TIME HERE.

43:36.748 --> 43:39.749
THE COFFEE, I GRANT YOU,
NEEDS IMPROVEMENT,

43:39.751 --> 43:41.117
BUT I TAKE EXCEPTION
TO THE IDEA

43:41.119 --> 43:42.852
THAT YOUR TIME HERE
IS WASTED.

43:42.854 --> 43:45.755
MY TIME,
MY CAREER, MY LIFE!

43:45.757 --> 43:47.123
I UNDERSTAND.
YOU'RE UPSET.

43:47.125 --> 43:49.092
I'M UPSET? YOU THINK?

43:49.094 --> 43:51.127
SEE IF YOU CAN
UNDERSTAND THIS--

43:51.129 --> 43:53.129
I QUIT.

43:54.098 --> 43:56.232
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

43:57.301 --> 43:59.035
SHANE?

43:59.037 --> 44:01.104
COME BACK, SHANE!

44:02.039 --> 44:05.141
OH, DEAR.

44:08.812 --> 44:10.246
UH...

44:10.248 --> 44:13.750
WELL, THERE IT IS.

44:16.053 --> 44:18.287
I BELIEVE I'VE ACCRUED
A BIT OF VACATION TIME,

44:18.289 --> 44:19.722
13 WEEKS,

44:19.724 --> 44:21.190
6 DAYS.

44:21.192 --> 44:23.826
I MAY TAKE A FEW MINUTES
OF THOSE NOW.

44:33.003 --> 44:35.872
[♪]

44:40.711 --> 44:42.712
THAT IS SO SWEET.

44:42.714 --> 44:43.880
WHAT?

44:43.882 --> 44:45.314
HE'S GOING AFTER HER.

44:45.316 --> 44:47.884
GOING AFTER HER WHAT?

44:50.287 --> 44:53.122
[♪]

45:03.000 --> 45:04.801
[BICYCLE BELL DINGS]

45:06.170 --> 45:08.871
[♪]

45:21.118 --> 45:23.453
[♪]

45:32.362 --> 45:34.163
[LAUGHS]

45:34.165 --> 45:36.065
REALLY?

45:36.067 --> 45:37.867
GAVE YOU 15 MINUTES
TO WALK TO THE PARK,

45:37.869 --> 45:39.902
FACTORED IN ANOTHER 10
FOR AIMLESS WANDERING,

45:39.904 --> 45:41.270
WHICH GAVE ME 25 MINUTES

45:41.272 --> 45:43.139
TO ORDER
YOUR SKINNY VANILLA LATTE

45:43.141 --> 45:45.341
AND DELIVER IT, STILL HOT,
BY THE TIME YOU SHOWED UP.

45:45.343 --> 45:48.411
SO YOU THINK I AM
THAT PREDICTABLE, HMM?

45:48.413 --> 45:52.348
NO. I THINK YOU'RE THAT INVESTED
IN YOUR WORK,

45:52.350 --> 45:54.217
AND AN EMPLOYEE
WITH THAT MUCH COMMITMENT

45:54.219 --> 45:56.185
SHOULD NOT BE ALLOWED
TO SELF-TERMINATE,

45:56.187 --> 45:58.921
OR DRINK SUB-STANDARD
SWILL, FOR THAT MATTER.

45:58.923 --> 45:59.922
[CUPS BONK]

45:59.924 --> 46:00.923
THANK YOU.

46:00.925 --> 46:02.024
MY PLEASURE.

46:02.026 --> 46:03.092
SHOULDN'T BE LONG NOW.

46:03.094 --> 46:04.794
MAILMAN'S
AROUND THE CORNER.

46:04.796 --> 46:05.895
JUST THINK.

46:05.897 --> 46:06.963
IN FIVE MINUTES,

46:06.965 --> 46:08.131
HE COULD BE
OPENING UP A LETTER,

46:08.133 --> 46:09.365
AND FINDING OUT
THAT HE HAS

46:09.367 --> 46:10.967
A DATE ON FRIDAY

46:10.969 --> 46:12.401
WITH THE LOVE
OF HIS LIFE.

46:12.403 --> 46:15.404
OR PERHAPS
HE HAS SINCE MET

46:15.406 --> 46:17.173
A WAITRESS
FROM OLIVE GARDEN,

46:17.175 --> 46:18.374
AND IS EXPECTING TWINS,

46:18.376 --> 46:19.909
AND TAKEN UP WORK

46:19.911 --> 46:21.878
AS A GROUTER
OF BATHROOM TILE.

46:21.880 --> 46:24.046
MM-MM, NO. NOT A CHANCE.
NOT OUR CHARLIE.

46:24.048 --> 46:26.082
OH. [CHUCKLES]

46:26.084 --> 46:28.351
MM. THERE IT IS.

46:28.353 --> 46:30.086
[♪]

46:30.088 --> 46:31.320
[SHANE SIGHS WISTFULLY]

46:31.322 --> 46:33.456
ONCE AGAIN,
CIVILIZATION PREVAILS.

46:33.458 --> 46:35.291
WAIT, WAIT. DON'T
YOU WANT TO SEE HIM...

46:35.293 --> 46:37.293
OPEN IT...

46:37.295 --> 46:39.929
[♪]

46:49.940 --> 46:52.875
[SHANE]: WHO IS THAT?

46:52.877 --> 46:55.077
WAIT...

46:55.079 --> 46:57.947
WHAT IS SHE DOING?

46:57.949 --> 46:59.415
WHAT IS SHE DOING?

46:59.417 --> 47:00.983
WHAT IS SHE DOING?

47:00.985 --> 47:03.019
UH... EXCUSE ME!

47:03.021 --> 47:04.220
MISS MC--

47:04.222 --> 47:05.988
UH, EXCUSE ME!

47:05.990 --> 47:09.091
HI! UH... MA'AM?

47:09.093 --> 47:11.861
UH, EXCUSE ME?
UM... HELLO.

47:11.863 --> 47:14.897
I AM FROM THE UNITED STATES
POSTAL SERVICE.

47:14.899 --> 47:17.166
I'M A DIRECT LINE OPERATIONS
SYSTEMS CONSULTANT,

47:17.168 --> 47:18.501
AND I AM CONDUCTING A...

47:18.503 --> 47:20.336
MAIL INVESTIGATION.

47:20.338 --> 47:21.971
I DON'T GET IT.

47:21.973 --> 47:24.073
YOU JUST REMOVED THAT ENVELOPE
FROM THE MAILBOX.

47:24.075 --> 47:27.343
SO? YOU DON'T HAVE TO MAKE
A FEDERAL CASE OUT OF IT.

47:27.345 --> 47:29.946
ACTUALLY, MAIL THEFT
IS A FEDERAL CASE, MA'AM.

47:29.948 --> 47:31.480
[LAUGHS] I'M NOT STEALING IT.

47:31.482 --> 47:33.516
I'M RETURNING IT.

47:33.518 --> 47:36.452
CHARLIE RIGGS
HAS BEEN GONE FOR A YEAR,

47:36.454 --> 47:38.588
AND I DON'T THINK
HE'S COMING BACK.

47:41.525 --> 47:44.961
I'M GOING TO
HAVE TO CONFISCATE THIS.

47:44.963 --> 47:46.329
CONFISCATE AWAY, HONEY.

47:46.331 --> 47:49.065
THANK YOU.

47:49.067 --> 47:51.234
WHAT?

47:54.071 --> 47:55.338
[SIGHS QUIETLY]

47:55.340 --> 47:57.139
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH THAT LETTER?

47:57.141 --> 47:58.908
YOU CAN'T JUST--

47:58.910 --> 48:00.476
READ IT.

48:00.478 --> 48:02.411
[♪]

48:02.413 --> 48:04.380
[NORMAN]:
WHAT DO YOU MEAN HE'S IN JAIL?

48:04.382 --> 48:07.250
I MEAN HIS NEIGHBOR WROTE
"NOT AT THIS ADDRESS. IN JAIL."

48:07.252 --> 48:08.918
ON THE ENVELOPE.

48:08.920 --> 48:12.154
YOU INTERCEPTED THE LETTER
AT THE POINT OF DELIVERY?

48:12.156 --> 48:13.956
-YEP.
ALTHOUGH 25 MINUTES EARLIER--

48:13.958 --> 48:15.992
...SHE HAD TENDERED
HER RESIGNATION,

48:15.994 --> 48:18.094
SO, TECHNICALLY, SHE HAD
YET TO BE REINSTATED

48:18.096 --> 48:19.428
AS A GOVERNMENT SERVANT.

48:19.430 --> 48:22.031
IT'S SHEER LUCK I WAS THERE
IN TIME TO INTERCEPT IT.

48:22.033 --> 48:24.100
LUCK IS THE RELIGION
OF THE LAZY.

48:25.068 --> 48:27.503
GUESS WHAT? I FOUND IT.
I STOPPED IT JUST IN TIME.

48:27.505 --> 48:29.138
YOUR CARD.

48:32.442 --> 48:34.076
IT'S FROM
YOUR DAD, RIGHT?

48:35.045 --> 48:38.514
AND THE HANDWRITING IS MALE,
LATE 40s, EARLY 50s.

48:42.185 --> 48:43.352
AREN'T YOU
GOING TO OPEN IT?

48:43.354 --> 48:44.453
MAYBE LATER.

48:44.455 --> 48:46.455
GOTTA FIND CHARLIE RIGGS FIRST.

48:46.457 --> 48:48.491
CHARLIE? KELLY'S CHARLIE?

48:48.493 --> 48:50.526
YEAH, CHARLIE-IN-JAIL-
FOR-SOMETHING CHARLIE.

48:50.528 --> 48:52.495
KNEW THERE WAS SOMETHING
FISHY ABOUT THAT GUY.

48:52.497 --> 48:54.030
SHH! I'M GOOGLING.

48:54.032 --> 48:56.065
BUT "CHARLIE RIGGS"
IS SUCH A NICE NAME.

48:56.067 --> 48:57.500
-OH, MY GOD!
-WHAT?

48:57.502 --> 48:59.468
DO YOU REMEMBER
THE BAKER ROGER PIPERSON,

48:59.470 --> 49:01.203
WHO WON THE LOTTERY?

49:01.205 --> 49:02.571
HE'S "THE LUCKIEST MAN
IN THE WORLD."

49:02.573 --> 49:05.041
ROGER PIPERSON WAS MURDERED...

49:05.043 --> 49:08.044
BY A MAN NAMED CHARLIE RIGGS.

49:08.046 --> 49:11.147
[♪]

49:16.186 --> 49:17.219
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

49:17.221 --> 49:19.288
WAIT! I REMEMBER.

49:19.290 --> 49:21.524
I READ AN ARTICLE
ABOUT THE BAKER IN PARK HILL.

49:21.526 --> 49:23.392
HE WAS GOING TO GIVE AWAY
ALL OF HIS LOTTERY MONEY

49:23.394 --> 49:24.493
TO AN ORPHANAGE

49:24.495 --> 49:26.228
IN LORETO HEIGHTS,
WHERE HE GREW UP.

49:26.230 --> 49:28.230
THEY SAID THAT HE WAS
A REAL SELF-MADE MAN.

49:28.232 --> 49:29.565
HE USED TO GIVE COOKIES

49:29.567 --> 49:31.434
TO THE KIDS EVERY DAY
AFTER SCHOOL.

49:31.436 --> 49:32.468
BUT THEN CHARLIE...

49:32.470 --> 49:34.403
NOT CHARLIE.

49:34.405 --> 49:35.638
RIGHT!

49:35.640 --> 49:38.174
SOMEONE, SOMEBODY,
WENT INTO THE BAKERY,

49:38.176 --> 49:40.242
SHOT THE BAKER, AND...

49:41.545 --> 49:43.045
AND WHAT?

49:43.047 --> 49:45.147
I STOPPED READING.

49:45.149 --> 49:47.249
IT WAS JUST TOO SAD.

49:47.251 --> 49:50.386
WELL, I DON'T
BELIEVE IT.

49:50.388 --> 49:52.154
NOT OUR CHARLIE.

49:52.156 --> 49:54.256
[OLIVER]:
HE'S NOT "OUR CHARLIE."

49:54.258 --> 49:55.491
AND IF IT'S TRUE,

49:55.493 --> 49:57.259
THEN PERHAPS KELLY MADE
THE RIGHT DECISION

49:57.261 --> 49:58.561
WHEN SHE DECIDED
TO WALK AWAY.

49:58.563 --> 50:01.430
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU JUST SAID THAT.

50:01.432 --> 50:03.532
I KNOW YOU WANT
THESE TWO TO BE HAPPY--

50:03.534 --> 50:05.368
NO. WAIT. HERE IT IS.

50:05.370 --> 50:07.403
<i>DETECTIVE ARTHUR KIMSEY OF</i>
<i>THE CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION UNIT</i>

50:07.405 --> 50:09.405
<i>SAID IT WAS THE SHORTEST</i>
<i>MURDER INVESTIGATION</i>

50:09.407 --> 50:11.374
<i>IN HIS 12 YEARS ON THE FORCE."</i>

50:11.376 --> 50:13.175
[DETECTIVE]:
<i>WE JUST WENT TO HIS HOUSE</i>

50:13.177 --> 50:14.577
<i>AND WAITED FOR HIM</i>
<i>TO COME HOME."</i>

50:14.579 --> 50:16.078
[REPORTER]:
<i>ACCORDING TO DETECTIVE KIMSEY,</i>

50:16.080 --> 50:17.413
<i>RIGGS WAS EASILY APPREHENDED</i>

50:17.415 --> 50:18.713
<i>BECAUSE HE NOT ONLY MATCHED</i>

50:18.715 --> 50:20.282
<i>THE DESCRIPTION</i>
<i>OF THE ALLEGED GUNMAN,</i>

50:20.284 --> 50:21.582
<i>BUT ALSO BECAUSE,</i>

50:21.584 --> 50:23.319
<i>IN HIS HASTE</i>
<i>TO ESCAPE THE SCENE,</i>

50:23.321 --> 50:25.554
<i>HE DROPPED HIS WALLET</i>
<i>AND IDENTIFICATION BEHIND.</i>

50:25.556 --> 50:28.124
OH, NO.
IT IS OUR CHARLIE.

50:28.126 --> 50:29.492
AH, HE'S NOT
BAD-LOOKIN'.

50:29.494 --> 50:31.527
[SHANE]: "RIGGS WAS
TAKEN INTO CUSTODY AND CHARGED

50:31.529 --> 50:33.129
"WITH SECOND-DEGREE MURDER

50:33.131 --> 50:34.296
"DURING THE COMMISSION
OF AN ARMED ROBBERY.

50:34.298 --> 50:36.265
"HE'S PLEADED "NOT GUILTY"

50:36.267 --> 50:38.334
"AND REMAINS
INCARCERATED WITHOUT BAIL,

50:38.336 --> 50:40.536
AND IS AWAITING TRIAL."

50:40.538 --> 50:43.072
WELL...

50:43.074 --> 50:44.640
THERE IT IS.

50:44.642 --> 50:46.776
[LID CLAPS SHUT]

50:47.711 --> 50:50.479
KELLY DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
IN HER LETTER

50:50.481 --> 50:52.348
ABOUT HIM BEING CLUMSY.

50:52.350 --> 50:54.383
[OLIVER]: OR HOMICIDAL.

50:54.385 --> 50:57.319
WAIT. WHAT DATE WAS THAT?

50:57.321 --> 51:00.256
LAST YEAR.
I THINK THIS MONTH...

51:00.258 --> 51:01.323
OH... WOW.

51:01.325 --> 51:02.458
OLIVER.

51:02.460 --> 51:04.493
IT HAPPENED A YEAR AGO
ON THE 26TH.

51:06.496 --> 51:08.397
I NEED A YOO-HOO.

51:09.366 --> 51:10.366
WHAT'S GOING ON?

51:10.368 --> 51:11.634
NORMAN, DON'T YOU GET IT?

51:11.636 --> 51:13.135
CHARLIE WAS WITH KELLY THAT DAY,

51:13.137 --> 51:15.137
ALL DAY,
AND HE DROPPED HIS WALLET,

51:15.139 --> 51:17.473
SO WHOEVER PICKED IT UP
PROBABLY SHOT THE BAKER.

51:17.475 --> 51:19.141
HE'S A LOT TALLER
THAN I THOUGHT HE WOULD BE.

51:19.143 --> 51:20.209
I WAS IN A JAIL ONCE.

51:20.211 --> 51:21.477
I WAS VISITING A COUSIN

51:21.479 --> 51:23.345
WHO WAS DOING 10 DAYS
IN QUARTZVILLE, ARIZONA--

51:23.347 --> 51:25.214
-...FOR TIPPING COWS.
-NORMAN, PLEASE STOP TALKING--

51:25.216 --> 51:27.283
...AND I MEAN IT FROM THE VERY
BOTTOM OF MY HEART, OKAY?

51:27.285 --> 51:30.653
"RIGGS FACES LIFE
IN LOTTERY-WINNER SHOOTING."

51:30.655 --> 51:32.655
OH, MY GOSH! HE GOES
TO TRIAL NEXT WEEK.

51:32.657 --> 51:34.356
WHAT ARE WE GOING TO DO?

51:34.358 --> 51:36.225
WE'RE GOING TO
RE-ADDRESS THE LETTER

51:36.227 --> 51:38.160
TO CHARLIE, CARE OF
THE COUNTY JAIL.

51:38.162 --> 51:40.496
THAT'S IT?
HE NEEDS OUR HELP!

51:40.498 --> 51:42.364
WELL, CLEARLY, HE
NEEDS SOMEONE'S HELP,

51:42.366 --> 51:44.233
LIKE HIS LAWYER,
FOR EXAMPLE,

51:44.235 --> 51:45.501
BUT THE U.S.
POSTAL SYSTEM

51:45.503 --> 51:47.369
IS NOT IN THE HABIT
OF DEFENDING MURDERERS.

51:47.371 --> 51:49.205
HE'S NOT A MURDERER!

51:49.207 --> 51:50.573
THAT'S RIGHT, AND WE KNOW THAT,
SO WE NEED TO DO SOMETHING.

51:50.575 --> 51:51.607
WELL, THE TRUTH IS,

51:51.609 --> 51:52.641
WE DON'T KNOW ANYTHING

51:52.643 --> 51:54.176
BEYOND WHAT'S IN
THE LETTER.

51:54.178 --> 51:55.211
VOILA!

51:55.213 --> 51:56.545
WHAT IS THIS?

51:56.547 --> 51:58.414
THIS IS JERRY POLEVICH,
CHARLIE'S PUBLIC DEFENDER,

51:58.416 --> 52:00.583
AND HE HAPPENS TO BE
ON A DATING WEBSITE.

52:00.585 --> 52:02.585
"JERRY POLEVICH, AGE 47.

52:02.587 --> 52:07.256
"EDUCATION: DEGREE IN LAW FROM
THE NORTH DENVER VALLEY COLLEGE.

52:07.258 --> 52:08.691
"RELIGION: NONE.

52:08.693 --> 52:11.260
"LANGUAGES:
'WHAT'S WRONG WITH ENGLISH?'

52:11.262 --> 52:12.394
STATUS: DIVORCED."

52:12.396 --> 52:14.730
THERE'S NO SURPRISE THERE,
IS THERE?

52:14.732 --> 52:18.534
"LIKES: GOLF, COOKING, GOLF,
EATING, GOLF,

52:18.536 --> 52:19.702
"BARBECUING, GOLF

52:19.704 --> 52:22.204
"AND ANYTHING
FROM THE MILE-HIGH DELI.

52:22.206 --> 52:23.772
"LIFE'S AMBITION:
TO QUIT THE LAW

52:23.774 --> 52:28.677
AND BUY THE BUNKER-SHOT GRILL
AT PINECOBBLE COUNTRY CLUB."

52:28.679 --> 52:30.546
THAT'S QUITE ENOUGH "GOOGLING,"
MS. McINERNEY.

52:30.548 --> 52:32.181
I'M CALLING THE RECEPTIONIST

52:32.183 --> 52:33.282
SO I CAN SET UP A MEETING
TO SIT DOWN FACE-TO--

52:33.284 --> 52:34.283
[JERRY]: <i>POLEVICH.</i>

52:34.285 --> 52:35.618
JERRY POLEVICH?

52:35.620 --> 52:38.354
JERRY POLEVICH, ESQUIRE?

52:38.356 --> 52:40.723
IF PERSONAL INJURY'S YOUR PLAN,
POLEVICH IS YOUR MAN.

52:40.725 --> 52:42.658
UH, I WILL KEEP THAT
IN MIND, SIR,

52:42.660 --> 52:45.594
BUT I'M NOT CALLING
TO SOLICIT YOUR SERVICES.

52:45.596 --> 52:48.197
I AM CALLING FROM
THE MAIN POST OFFICE DOWN--

52:48.199 --> 52:49.431
AH! GREAT!
YOU FOUND 'EM!

52:49.433 --> 52:51.300
I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU GUYS
COULD MANAGE TO LOSE

52:51.302 --> 52:53.802
60 POUNDS OF MAIL-ORDER STEAK
ON DRY ICE.

52:53.804 --> 52:56.772
THE UNITED STATES POST OFFICE
DOES NOT "LOSE" THINGS, SIR.

52:56.774 --> 52:58.507
LOOK, IF-IF YOU DON'T
WANNA SUE ANYBODY,

52:58.509 --> 52:59.742
YOU DON'T GOT MY STEAK,

52:59.744 --> 53:00.843
WHAT DO YA WANT?

53:00.845 --> 53:04.213
WELL, I'M CALLING
WITH INFORMATION

53:04.215 --> 53:05.414
ABOUT THE MAN WHO KILLED--

53:05.416 --> 53:06.515
ALLEGEDLY!

53:06.517 --> 53:09.785
...ALLEGEDLY KILLED
ROGER PIPERSON.

53:09.787 --> 53:10.719
WHO?

53:10.721 --> 53:12.321
CHARLES RIGGS.

53:12.323 --> 53:14.456
YOU ARE HIS PUBLIC DEFENDER,
ARE YOU NOT?

53:14.458 --> 53:17.693
CHARLES RIGGS?
WELL, THEN WHO'S ROGER PIPERSON?

53:17.695 --> 53:19.328
THE BAKER!

53:19.330 --> 53:21.330
WHO WAS UNFORTUNATELY
DISPATCHED... LAST YEAR.

53:21.332 --> 53:22.865
OH, RIGHT, RIGHT,
RIGHT, RIGHT.

53:22.867 --> 53:24.533
THE PIPERSON BAKERY.

53:24.535 --> 53:25.734
OH! I LOVED THAT BAKERY!

53:25.736 --> 53:27.436
I HAVEN'T HAD
A DECENT BEARCLAW SINCE.

53:27.438 --> 53:28.571
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

53:28.573 --> 53:29.805
WELL, I HAVE PROOF--

53:29.807 --> 53:31.840
A LETTER DETAILING
CHARLES RIGGS' ACTIVITIES

53:31.842 --> 53:33.609
THE DAY THE BAKER WAS DISPATCHED

53:33.611 --> 53:36.312
WHICH PROVES HIS INNOCENCE
INCONTROVERTI...

53:36.314 --> 53:37.846
LOOK, LOOK, PAL.
ANYBODY CAN WRITE A LETTER.

53:37.848 --> 53:39.682
DO YOU GOT ANY PICTURES? VIDEO?

53:39.684 --> 53:41.383
NO.

53:41.385 --> 53:42.718
WELL, THAT'S WHAT
I'M GONNA NEED.

53:42.720 --> 53:44.887
YOU GET ME MY VISUALS
AND MY 60 POUNDS OF STEAK,

53:44.889 --> 53:46.822
THEN WE'LL TALK.

53:47.791 --> 53:49.658
YOU STILL WANNA
DO NOTHING, OLIVER?

53:49.660 --> 53:52.394
YOU WANNA LEAVE IT UP
TO THE CRACK LEGAL MIND

53:52.396 --> 53:53.762
OF A MAN WHO BUYS HIS MEAT
THROUGH THE MAIL?

53:53.764 --> 53:55.898
NO, OF COURSE NOT,
BUT WE HAVE NO ALTERNATIVE.

53:55.900 --> 53:57.733
WRONG.

53:57.735 --> 53:59.501
THE OTHER DAY,

53:59.503 --> 54:00.903
YOU SAID THAT
WE ARE RESPONSIBLE

54:00.905 --> 54:02.638
FOR WHAT LITTLE
TRUTH WE HAVE.

54:02.640 --> 54:03.872
WELL, THE TRUTH IS,

54:03.874 --> 54:05.874
CHARLIE RIGGS IS INNOCENT
AND WE CAN PROVE IT.

54:05.876 --> 54:07.443
POSSIBLY.

54:07.445 --> 54:08.477
POSSIBLY? PROBABLY!

54:08.479 --> 54:09.878
AND WE HAVE
A MORAL OBLIGATION

54:09.880 --> 54:11.413
TO AT LEAST TRY.

54:11.415 --> 54:12.815
WHAT ARE YOU PROPOSING?

54:12.817 --> 54:16.318
WE KNOW POLEVICH WON'T DO
ANYTHING WITH THE LETTER, RIGHT?

54:16.320 --> 54:19.688
BUT IF WE DELIVER
THE LETTER TO CHARLIE IN PERSON,

54:19.690 --> 54:22.891
MAYBE HE CAN TELL US SOMETHING
THAT WE CAN DO TO HELP HIM.

54:22.893 --> 54:24.827
CHARLIE NEEDS THIS LETTER.

54:26.496 --> 54:28.497
HE NEEDS TO KEEP
THAT DATE WITH KELLY

54:28.499 --> 54:30.899
AND HE NEEDS A FRIEND.

54:30.901 --> 54:33.569
I KNOW IT'S RISKY,

54:33.571 --> 54:34.837
BUT...

54:34.839 --> 54:37.506
SOMETIMES, YOU JUST
HAVE TO TAKE THE LEAP.

54:37.508 --> 54:39.675
-IT'S A COMPELLING PROPOSITION.
-LOOK--

54:39.677 --> 54:41.910
WITH MY COMPUTER SKILLS,
RITA'S MEMORY,

54:41.912 --> 54:44.546
YOUR GENIUS
AS A POSTAL DETECTIVE,

54:44.548 --> 54:48.450
AND NORMAN'S EXPERTISE
AT... SO MANY THINGS...

54:48.452 --> 54:49.818
[CHUCKLES SHYLY]

54:49.820 --> 54:51.920
THINK OF US AS A...

54:51.922 --> 54:54.423
COVERT DIVISION
OF POSTAL INTELLIGENCE.

54:54.425 --> 54:55.658
LIKE SECRET AGENTS?

54:56.693 --> 54:58.427
I ONCE APPLIED TO THE C.I.A.

54:58.429 --> 54:59.962
ME TOO! I DIDN'T GET IN.

54:59.964 --> 55:01.830
THERE'S ALSO THE PROBLEM
OF ANDREA, OF COURSE.

55:01.832 --> 55:03.565
SHE'LL WANT TO KNOW
WHAT WE'RE UP TO.

55:03.567 --> 55:05.734
WELL, WE SIMPLY TELL HER
THAT WE ARE FACT-GATHERING

55:05.736 --> 55:07.536
TO ENSURE THE DELIVERY
OF LETTERS

55:07.538 --> 55:09.338
THAT REQUIRE
SPECIAL HANDLING.

55:09.340 --> 55:11.340
SHE COULD CONFISCATE
MY REFRIGERATOR.

55:11.342 --> 55:12.675
WE'LL BE FLYING
UNDER THE RADAR.

55:12.677 --> 55:14.710
"POSTAL INTELLIGENCE."

55:17.580 --> 55:20.449
I SUPPOSE WE ARE THAT...

55:20.451 --> 55:21.550
ALREADY.

55:21.552 --> 55:24.520
EXCEPT NOW
WE WOULD HAVE...

55:24.522 --> 55:26.822
WELL, WE WOULD
HAVE A LICENSE TO...

55:26.824 --> 55:27.890
...TO DELIVER!

55:27.892 --> 55:28.791
YES!

55:28.793 --> 55:30.959
A LICENSE TO DELIVER.

55:32.595 --> 55:34.029
[CLINKING]

55:41.471 --> 55:43.539
[♪]

55:43.541 --> 55:44.540
ALRIGHT, LET'S DO
FINAL CHECKS.

55:44.542 --> 55:45.541
UH, TRENCH COAT?

55:45.543 --> 55:46.542
CHECK.

55:46.544 --> 55:47.609
LAPTOP.

55:47.611 --> 55:48.610
CHECK.

55:48.612 --> 55:49.578
GAS IN THE JAG?

55:49.580 --> 55:50.546
CHECK.

55:50.548 --> 55:51.513
WE'RE TAKING THAT?

55:51.515 --> 55:52.648
V-12 XJS.

55:52.650 --> 55:53.882
NOBODY WHO WORKS
FOR THE GOVERNMENT

55:53.884 --> 55:54.883
DRIVES A CAR LIKE THAT
EXCEPT JAMES BOND.

55:54.885 --> 55:55.951
I'LL TAKE THAT
AS A COMPLIMENT.

55:55.953 --> 55:57.920
OH! SHE'S COMING!

55:57.922 --> 55:59.755
GO. GO!

56:00.957 --> 56:02.591
WHERE'S OLIVER?

56:02.593 --> 56:03.792
GOOD MORNING, ANDREA.

56:03.794 --> 56:04.993
[CLAPS SHUT]

56:04.995 --> 56:07.463
[CART RUMBLING]

56:08.765 --> 56:10.933
NORMAN?

56:10.935 --> 56:13.035
WHAT IN THE NAME OF PAUL REVERE
ARE YOU DOING?

56:13.037 --> 56:14.403
SORTING.
FORWARDING.

56:14.405 --> 56:15.703
THE USUAL.

56:15.805 --> 56:19.007
TELL OLIVER I WANT HIM IN
THE DEPARTMENT MEETING. PRONTO.

56:19.009 --> 56:21.510
OH, OLIVER ACTUALLY WENT HOME.

56:21.512 --> 56:25.714
HE GOT HOLD OF A BAD PIECE
OF... FISH LAST NIGHT.

56:25.716 --> 56:26.715
THEN SEND
THAT OTHER ONE.

56:26.717 --> 56:27.783
WELL, THAT COULD
BE A PROBLEM.

56:27.785 --> 56:29.518
SAME DINNER.

56:29.520 --> 56:31.587
SAME FISH.

56:32.655 --> 56:34.923
I WANT ONE OF THEM
IN THAT DEPARTMENT MEETING,

56:34.925 --> 56:39.762
AND NOBODY GOES HOME SICK
UNLESS I SEND THEM HOME SICK!

56:41.865 --> 56:43.732
[SIGHING]

56:43.734 --> 56:46.068
[DOORS SWINGING SHUT]

56:46.070 --> 56:47.803
WHEN SHE WAS
"MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY,"

56:47.805 --> 56:50.038
SHE SANG "CLIMB EVERY MOUNTAIN"
FOR HER TALENT SECTION.

56:51.474 --> 56:55.644
LIFE CAN TAKE A TOLL
ON A WOMAN WITHOUT LOVE, NORMAN.

56:56.613 --> 56:59.081
[♪]

57:02.585 --> 57:03.786
HI THERE.

57:03.788 --> 57:06.555
WE HAVE AN ATTORNEY/CLIENT
CONSULTATION

57:06.557 --> 57:08.023
WITH PRISONER CHARLES RIGGS.

57:08.025 --> 57:10.793
-I.D..
-YES.

57:11.961 --> 57:13.028
HERE YOU ARE.

57:15.899 --> 57:18.734
I DON'T SEE YOUR NAMES
ON TODAY'S LIST.

57:18.736 --> 57:22.571
OH? UH...
WHAT LIST IS THAT?

57:22.573 --> 57:24.973
CLIENT-COUNSEL
APPOINTMENT ROSTER.

57:24.975 --> 57:29.111
AH! THE CLIENT-COUNSEL
APPOINTMENT ROSTER?

57:29.113 --> 57:31.547
I PUT OUR NAMES
ON THAT YESTERDAY.

57:31.549 --> 57:33.615
YOU WOULD HAVE HAD TO HAVE
DONE THAT LAST THURSDAY.

57:33.617 --> 57:34.716
THAT WHAT I MEANT.

57:34.718 --> 57:36.718
I PUT OUR NAMES
ON THAT ON THURSDAY.

57:36.720 --> 57:37.753
FOR TODAY.

57:37.755 --> 57:38.987
THURSDAY.

57:38.989 --> 57:40.556
THAT WAS A LOVELY
DAY, WASN'T IT?

57:40.558 --> 57:41.723
MM! GORGEOUS.

57:41.725 --> 57:42.825
VIRTUALLY CLOUDLESS.

57:42.827 --> 57:43.926
BEAUTIFUL.

57:43.928 --> 57:46.829
YEAH, WOULD YOU MIND
CHECKING AGAIN?

57:48.765 --> 57:51.600
OKAY. THERE YOU ARE,

57:51.602 --> 57:54.002
BUT I DON'T SEE YOU
AS THE ATTORNEY-OF-RECORD.

57:54.004 --> 57:57.139
OH! YOU ARE, OF COURSE,
REFERRING TO JERRY POLEVICH.

57:57.141 --> 57:58.607
A FINE FELLOW.

57:58.609 --> 57:59.842
ALWAYS BEEN PLEASED
WITH HIS WORK.

57:59.844 --> 58:01.109
SADLY, HOWEVER,

58:01.111 --> 58:04.546
HE WAS PLACED
ON ADMINISTRATIVE LEAVE

58:04.548 --> 58:09.651
AFTER INHALING A FEW TOO MANY
MILE-HIGH PASTRAMI PLATTERS.

58:09.653 --> 58:10.953
I UNDERSTAND, I UNDERSTAND.

58:10.955 --> 58:13.522
WELL, JERRY DOES LIKE HIS DELI,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

58:13.524 --> 58:15.657
YES, HE DOES.

58:15.659 --> 58:16.792
THANK YOU.

58:16.794 --> 58:17.893
THANK YOU.

58:19.762 --> 58:22.865
[♪]

58:28.705 --> 58:30.906
DO I KNOW YOU?

58:30.908 --> 58:31.974
NO, CHARLIE,
YOU DON'T,

58:31.976 --> 58:32.941
BUT WE'RE HERE
TO HELP YOU.

58:32.943 --> 58:34.643
FINALLY.

58:34.645 --> 58:35.944
YOU'RE FROM THE STATE LEGAL
ASSISTANCE OFFICE, RIGHT?

58:35.946 --> 58:38.146
ACTUALLY, WE'RE FROM
THE U.S. POST OFFICE.

58:40.583 --> 58:42.050
[QUIET GASP]

58:42.052 --> 58:43.652
I KNEW SOMETHING WAS WRONG.

58:43.654 --> 58:47.122
I KNEW SHE WOULD'VE COME FORWARD
IF SHE COULD'VE.

58:49.926 --> 58:52.794
EVERYBODY
THOUGHT I MADE HER UP,

58:52.796 --> 58:54.897
BUT NOW I'VE GOT PROOF.

58:54.899 --> 58:57.666
ONLY PROOF THAT
SHE LOVED YOU, I'M AFRAID.

58:57.668 --> 59:00.168
AND I'M AFRAID
YOU CAN'T PROVE ANYTHING ELSE

59:00.170 --> 59:01.703
ABOUT THAT DAY

59:01.705 --> 59:03.972
WITHOUT HER
AND THE PICTURES SHE TOOK.

59:03.974 --> 59:07.075
[SHANE]: ALL YOU NEED IS ONE
PHOTO WITH KELLY FROM THAT DAY.

59:07.077 --> 59:10.946
MAYBE ONE WITH THE BLOODMOBILE
THAT ONLY HAPPENS ONCE A Y--

59:10.948 --> 59:12.948
ONCE A YEAR IN THE PARK!
THAT'D BE PERFECT.

59:12.950 --> 59:14.616
NOW, ON THE 26TH--

59:14.618 --> 59:16.218
ON THE 26TH,
I'LL STILL BE HERE.

59:17.220 --> 59:19.154
THEN WE'LL GO FOR YOU.

59:19.156 --> 59:21.089
WE'LL KEEP THAT DATE
ON THE BRIDGE.

59:21.091 --> 59:22.758
WE'LL MEET KELLY,

59:22.760 --> 59:24.092
AND WE'LL GET THE PICTURES,
AND WE'LL LET YOU KNOW

59:24.094 --> 59:26.194
AS SOON AS WE GET THEM.

59:27.196 --> 59:28.997
I JUST WANT TO KNOW
IF SHE'S OKAY.

59:28.999 --> 59:31.833
I WISH I KNEW
WHAT WAS WRONG WITH HER.

59:31.835 --> 59:33.869
WE COULD MAKE SOME...

59:33.871 --> 59:35.203
DISCREET INQUIRIES.

59:35.205 --> 59:37.105
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
YOU CAN TELL US ABOUT HER

59:37.107 --> 59:39.308
THAT WASN'T
IN THAT LETTER?

59:40.843 --> 59:43.712
WELL, I REMEMBER
WHEN SHE GOT ON THE ELEVATOR,

59:43.714 --> 59:45.614
SHE HAD
THESE BEAUTIFUL EYES.

59:45.616 --> 59:46.915
CHARLIE, DO YOU REMEMBER

59:46.917 --> 59:49.251
WHAT FLOOR
SHE GOT ON IN THE ELEVATOR?

59:49.253 --> 59:52.788
I-- I THINK
IT WAS THE THIRD FLOOR.

59:52.790 --> 59:54.122
THAT WAS THE COLORADO BANK
BUILDING, RIGHT?

59:54.124 --> 59:56.024
YEAH, I THINK. WHY?

59:56.026 --> 59:58.894
JUST GIVE ME A SECOND.

59:58.896 --> 1:00:01.930
OKAY, HERE IT IS.
SUITE 305.

1:00:01.932 --> 1:00:03.198
WESTERN STATES
RESEARCH SYSTEMS.

1:00:03.200 --> 1:00:05.000
"A STATE-OF-THE-ART
MEDICAL RESEARCH COMPANY

1:00:05.002 --> 1:00:07.069
"SPECIALIZING
IN THE EXPERIMENTAL TREATMENT

1:00:07.071 --> 1:00:08.136
"OF BLOOD-RELATED DISORDERS.

1:00:08.138 --> 1:00:10.005
SPECIFICALLY..."
[INHALES SHARPLY]

1:00:10.007 --> 1:00:12.808
"HODGKIN'S DISEASE."

1:00:14.177 --> 1:00:16.244
OH, MY GOD.

1:00:16.246 --> 1:00:18.213
CHECK TO SEE IF
ANY PATIENTS NAMED KELLY

1:00:18.215 --> 1:00:20.983
PARTICIPATED
IN AN EXPERIMENTAL TREATMENT

1:00:20.985 --> 1:00:22.217
LAST YEAR.

1:00:22.219 --> 1:00:23.885
I'M ON IT.

1:00:23.887 --> 1:00:25.253
I TRIED TO LOOK HER UP ONLINE,
BUT... [SCOFFS]

1:00:25.255 --> 1:00:28.724
I EVEN LOOKED FOR
A CHARLIE-AND-KELLY WEBSITE.

1:00:28.726 --> 1:00:29.725
OKAY. I'M IN.

1:00:29.727 --> 1:00:31.893
JUNE 26TH, LAST YEAR,

1:00:31.895 --> 1:00:33.893
THEY FINALIZED
THEIR CONTROL GROUP

1:00:33.895 --> 1:00:36.064
OF 40 PATIENTS WITH
STAGE-3B HODGKIN'S LYMPHOMA

1:00:36.066 --> 1:00:38.767
AND STARTED DOUBLE-BLIND TRIALS
THE NEXT DAY,

1:00:38.769 --> 1:00:40.869
SO THEY USED ONLY FIRST NAMES.

1:00:40.871 --> 1:00:42.037
JACK, AGE 30.

1:00:42.039 --> 1:00:43.672
JASON, AGE 29.

1:00:43.674 --> 1:00:45.707
KELLY, AGE 23.
THAT'S GOT TO BE HER, RIGHT?

1:00:45.709 --> 1:00:46.742
YEAH.

1:00:46.744 --> 1:00:49.177
OKAY, LET'S SEE
HOW SHE'S DOING.

1:00:49.179 --> 1:00:51.113
[KEYS CLACK, THEN STOP]

1:00:58.921 --> 1:01:00.989
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

1:01:05.328 --> 1:01:09.131
"THE SIX-MONTH CLINICAL TRIAL
COMMENCING JUNE 27th

1:01:09.133 --> 1:01:12.100
"FAILED TO PRODUCE
POSITIVE OUTCOMES

1:01:12.102 --> 1:01:15.203
"IN 100% OF THE SUBJECTS.

1:01:15.205 --> 1:01:17.172
"AS OF THIS DATE,

1:01:17.174 --> 1:01:19.841
NO PATIENTS
SURVIVED TREATMENT."

1:01:19.843 --> 1:01:22.978
[♪]

1:01:25.948 --> 1:01:28.216
I, UH...

1:01:29.919 --> 1:01:31.153
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.

1:01:31.155 --> 1:01:32.954
CHARLIE...

1:01:32.956 --> 1:01:35.424
IT MEANS SHE'S GONE.

1:01:42.098 --> 1:01:44.900
I'M SO SORRY, CHARLIE.

1:01:53.976 --> 1:01:56.978
[♪]

1:02:03.319 --> 1:02:06.288
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO NOW?

1:02:06.290 --> 1:02:09.024
THE PICTURES HAVE TO
BE OUT THERE SOMEWHERE.

1:02:09.026 --> 1:02:10.358
WE DIDN'T TRY
HARD ENOUGH.

1:02:10.360 --> 1:02:12.260
WE COULD HAVE--

1:02:12.262 --> 1:02:14.129
NO. WE TRIED,
WE DID OUR BEST.

1:02:14.131 --> 1:02:17.833
NOW WE HAVE TO DO
WHAT WE KNOW HOW TO DO

1:02:17.835 --> 1:02:20.068
AND LET CHARLIE GRIEVE
FOR KELLY.

1:02:20.070 --> 1:02:21.303
AND FIGHT
FOR HIS LIFE.

1:02:21.305 --> 1:02:22.904
[DOOR BANGS OPEN]

1:02:22.906 --> 1:02:25.874
GOTTEN OVER
THE BAD FISH, I SEE.

1:02:25.876 --> 1:02:27.776
YEAH! [CHUCKLES]

1:02:27.778 --> 1:02:29.144
IT'S A MIRACLE.

1:02:29.146 --> 1:02:32.147
FORGIVE ME FOR NOT KEEPING YOU
IN THE LOOP, ANDREA.

1:02:32.149 --> 1:02:33.281
YEAH.

1:02:33.283 --> 1:02:36.084
I REALLY MISSED
BEING IN YOUR LOOP.

1:02:36.086 --> 1:02:38.286
TOO BAD YOU WEREN'T IN MINE.

1:02:38.288 --> 1:02:40.255
YOU DIDN'T GO
TO THE MEETING.

1:02:40.257 --> 1:02:43.091
AND I REGRET THAT.
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

1:02:43.093 --> 1:02:45.327
YOU'RE DARN RIGHT
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN,

1:02:45.329 --> 1:02:47.796
'CAUSE THERE AIN'T GONNA BE
ANOTHER DEPARTMENT MEETING.

1:02:47.798 --> 1:02:48.864
EVER.

1:02:50.299 --> 1:02:52.067
BEG YOUR PARDON?

1:02:52.069 --> 1:02:54.202
THEY'RE SHUTTING
THE PLACE DOWN.

1:02:54.204 --> 1:02:55.937
YEAH.

1:02:55.939 --> 1:02:59.007
THIS LOUSY, SMELLY OFFICE HAS--

1:02:59.009 --> 1:03:00.842
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

1:03:00.844 --> 1:03:02.210
"LOST ITS VIABILITY."

1:03:02.212 --> 1:03:06.181
THE DEAD LETTER OFFICE
IS... DEAD?

1:03:06.183 --> 1:03:07.415
THIS TIME NEXT MONTH,

1:03:07.417 --> 1:03:09.317
YOU ALL WILL BE SELLING STAMPS

1:03:09.319 --> 1:03:12.187
AND SORTING CATALOGUES
IN PUEBLO.

1:03:12.189 --> 1:03:13.822
YOU WANTED A TRANSFER?

1:03:13.824 --> 1:03:16.057
YOU'RE GONNA GET ONE, MISSY.

1:03:16.059 --> 1:03:17.225
[CHUCKLES]

1:03:17.227 --> 1:03:19.494
HOW'S THAT
FOR BEING IN THE LOOP?

1:03:23.933 --> 1:03:27.269
[DOOR SWINGS OPEN AND SHUT]

1:03:30.473 --> 1:03:33.208
[♪]

1:03:33.210 --> 1:03:36.011
TODAY WAS
A VERY BAD DAY.

1:03:36.013 --> 1:03:37.946
I THOUGHT WE WERE
A PRETTY GOOD TEAM,

1:03:37.948 --> 1:03:39.247
HOLDING DOWN
THE FORT.

1:03:40.216 --> 1:03:41.516
HEY, NORMAN,
DO YOU WANNA DANCE?

1:03:43.186 --> 1:03:48.023
UH... COULD WE PLAY
SHUFFLEBOARD INSTEAD?

1:03:48.025 --> 1:03:50.358
OKAY.

1:03:55.031 --> 1:03:56.865
SHE HAS A TERRIBLE
CRUSH ON HIM.

1:03:56.867 --> 1:03:58.099
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

1:03:58.101 --> 1:04:00.235
THAT'S VERY INSIGHTFUL,

1:04:00.237 --> 1:04:03.905
CONSIDERING SHE
ABSOLUTELY TERRIFIES HIM.

1:04:03.907 --> 1:04:05.941
YEAH, WELL,
LOVE IS FUNNY.

1:04:05.943 --> 1:04:07.976
ODD, PERHAPS.

1:04:07.978 --> 1:04:10.111
BUT FUNNY?

1:04:10.113 --> 1:04:12.180
RARELY.

1:04:14.951 --> 1:04:16.051
OH, LOOK.

1:04:16.053 --> 1:04:18.486
DRINKS ARE HERE,
FINALLY.

1:04:18.488 --> 1:04:21.122
TO, UM...

1:04:22.058 --> 1:04:23.992
TO THE DEAD LETTER OFFICE--

1:04:23.994 --> 1:04:26.995
THE LAST HOPE
OF THE WRITTEN WORD.

1:04:26.997 --> 1:04:28.129
[CLINK]

1:04:29.165 --> 1:04:31.399
[CHUCKLES]

1:04:35.238 --> 1:04:37.973
I WENT ON
A PILGRIMAGE

1:04:37.975 --> 1:04:39.407
TO THE NATIONAL
POSTAL MUSEUM

1:04:39.409 --> 1:04:40.442
TWO YEARS AGO.

1:04:40.444 --> 1:04:44.212
IT WAS GLORIOUS.

1:04:44.214 --> 1:04:45.914
[SHANE CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1:04:45.916 --> 1:04:48.350
I CAN'T SAY
THAT I EVER WENT.

1:04:48.352 --> 1:04:50.285
I GOT LOST IN IT.

1:04:50.287 --> 1:04:52.320
DID YOU GO ALONE?

1:04:52.322 --> 1:04:54.155
NO.

1:04:54.157 --> 1:04:55.457
WELL, SORT OF.

1:04:55.459 --> 1:04:57.492
I TOOK MY WIFE.

1:04:57.494 --> 1:05:00.295
A LOVELY PERSON
WHOSE INTERESTS

1:05:00.297 --> 1:05:03.031
EXTENDED FAR BEYOND
THE WRITTEN WORD

1:05:03.033 --> 1:05:05.066
TO, SHALL WE SAY...

1:05:05.068 --> 1:05:07.302
THE SOMEWHAT DECADENT.

1:05:08.271 --> 1:05:13.074
WE WERE STANDING IN FRONT OF
THE PONY EXPRESS EXHIBIT.

1:05:13.076 --> 1:05:15.310
I TURNED AROUND,

1:05:15.312 --> 1:05:18.380
SHE WASN'T THERE ANYMORE.

1:05:19.448 --> 1:05:22.284
I LOOKED
EVERYWHERE FOR HER.

1:05:26.522 --> 1:05:28.189
I FINALLY GAVE UP.

1:05:28.191 --> 1:05:30.325
I WENT BACK TO
THE HOLIDAY INN EXPRESS

1:05:30.327 --> 1:05:34.596
AND, UM, WAITED FOR HER.

1:05:34.598 --> 1:05:37.132
SHE NEVER CAME.

1:05:38.968 --> 1:05:40.368
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO CALL THE POLICE

1:05:40.370 --> 1:05:42.003
WHEN I NOTICED

1:05:42.005 --> 1:05:45.540
THAT LITTLE RED LIGHT BLINKING
ON THE PHONE.

1:05:49.045 --> 1:05:51.012
SHE LEFT THIS MESSAGE.

1:05:51.014 --> 1:05:53.181
SHE SAID
THAT SHE WAS TIRED

1:05:53.183 --> 1:05:56.318
OF BEING MARRIED
TO A GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL,

1:05:56.320 --> 1:05:59.220
AND SHE FIGURED,
SINCE SHE WAS IN WASHINGTON, DC,

1:05:59.222 --> 1:06:01.389
IT WAS THE CLOSEST
SHE HAD EVER BEEN TO PARIS,

1:06:01.391 --> 1:06:04.592
SO SHE WAS GETTING ON A PLANE
AND MOVING TO FRANCE.

1:06:07.129 --> 1:06:09.531
[DEFLATING SIGH]

1:06:11.000 --> 1:06:13.535
I'M SO SORRY, OLIVER.

1:06:13.537 --> 1:06:15.370
[SIGHS]

1:06:15.372 --> 1:06:17.339
DID SHE EVER COME BACK?

1:06:17.341 --> 1:06:19.607
NOT YET.

1:06:22.378 --> 1:06:25.547
THE LAST THING SHE SAID
ON HER MESSAGE WAS,

1:06:25.549 --> 1:06:27.615
"I'LL SEND YOU
MY FORWARDING ADDRESS.

1:06:27.617 --> 1:06:29.184
<i>AU REVOIR."</i>

1:06:29.186 --> 1:06:30.452
ACTUALLY,
SHE PRONOUNCED IT

1:06:30.454 --> 1:06:32.654
"OR REV-OR."

1:06:32.656 --> 1:06:38.293
BUT I ASSUME HER ACCENT'S
MUCH IMPROVED BY NOW.

1:06:42.031 --> 1:06:45.500
DON'T YOU THINK YOU'VE WAITED
FOR HER LONG ENOUGH?

1:06:46.469 --> 1:06:49.537
I BELIEVE IN KEEPING PROMISES.

1:06:50.606 --> 1:06:53.375
I AM, AFTER ALL,
A GENTLEMAN.

1:06:56.545 --> 1:06:59.180
THAT YOU ARE.

1:07:06.355 --> 1:07:08.690
OLIVER?

1:07:08.692 --> 1:07:11.593
WOULD YOU LIKE TO DANCE?

1:07:12.561 --> 1:07:14.629
[LAUGHING]

1:07:19.068 --> 1:07:21.369
[♪]

1:07:28.411 --> 1:07:31.746
HAVE YOU EVER THOUGHT
ABOUT JUST GOING TO PARIS?

1:07:33.215 --> 1:07:36.117
SADLY, I LACK
THE PROPER LUGGAGE.

1:07:36.119 --> 1:07:38.186
OR YOU COULD
JUST GIVE ME HER NAME

1:07:38.188 --> 1:07:39.487
AND I'LL LOOK HER UP
IN 10 SECONDS,

1:07:39.489 --> 1:07:42.424
AND THEN YOU'D
FINALLY KNOW.

1:07:42.426 --> 1:07:45.427
I SUPPOSE I WOULD.

1:07:48.364 --> 1:07:51.166
YOU KNOW,
I BET THAT'S IT.

1:07:51.168 --> 1:07:53.435
YOU ESCHEW
THE ELECTRONIC AGE,

1:07:53.437 --> 1:07:55.570
BECAUSE IF YOU KNEW...

1:07:55.572 --> 1:07:58.506
LOVE THAT WORD. "ESCHEW."

1:08:00.743 --> 1:08:03.178
[♪]

1:08:05.281 --> 1:08:08.216
YOU REJECT IT ALL,

1:08:08.218 --> 1:08:12.220
BECAUSE IF YOU KNEW
HOW TO GOOGLE AND SKYPE

1:08:12.222 --> 1:08:14.556
AND TWEET
AND THAT STUFF,

1:08:14.558 --> 1:08:16.291
YOU WOULD NO LONGER
HAVE AN EXCUSE

1:08:16.293 --> 1:08:17.759
FOR NOT FACING
THE TRUTH.

1:08:17.761 --> 1:08:21.362
PLEASE DON'T PSYCHOANALYZE
THE SECTION LEADER.

1:08:21.364 --> 1:08:23.398
BESIDES,
YOU'RE ONE TO TALK.

1:08:23.400 --> 1:08:25.567
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

1:08:25.569 --> 1:08:30.271
WELL, WHY HAVEN'T
YOU OPENED YOUR CARD YET?

1:08:30.273 --> 1:08:31.773
HMM?

1:08:31.775 --> 1:08:34.242
YOU SHOULD OPEN IT.

1:08:34.244 --> 1:08:36.644
MY GUESS IS
A BIRTHDAY CARD

1:08:36.646 --> 1:08:39.247
FROM DADDY WITH A...

1:08:39.249 --> 1:08:40.448
20 IN IT.

1:08:40.450 --> 1:08:42.851
[♪]

1:08:46.355 --> 1:08:48.423
YOU ARE GOOD.

1:08:50.659 --> 1:08:55.730
YEAH. HE ALWAYS SENT ME
$20 FOR MY BIRTHDAY.

1:08:57.266 --> 1:08:59.167
SENT.

1:08:59.169 --> 1:09:00.668
NOT GAVE?

1:09:02.805 --> 1:09:06.341
HE LEFT US
WHEN I WAS 10.

1:09:07.309 --> 1:09:09.777
HE ALWAYS PROMISED
TO COME TO MY BIRTHDAY,

1:09:09.779 --> 1:09:13.314
BUT ALL I EVER GOT WAS
A CARD AND SOME MONEY.

1:09:13.316 --> 1:09:14.582
THAT'S WHY...

1:09:14.584 --> 1:09:18.286
MAKING SURE KELLY AND CHARLIE
KEPT THAT DATE

1:09:18.288 --> 1:09:19.554
MEANT SO MUCH TO YOU.

1:09:19.556 --> 1:09:21.823
YEAH, MAYBE.

1:09:24.760 --> 1:09:28.630
I KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE TO WAIT
FOR SOMEONE WHO NEVER COMES.

1:09:31.267 --> 1:09:34.536
[WHISPERS]:
I'M SORRY FOR YOU.

1:09:35.738 --> 1:09:39.641
LIFE IS SHORT,
MS. McINERNEY.

1:09:39.643 --> 1:09:41.209
[SNIFFLES DEEPLY]

1:09:41.211 --> 1:09:43.244
PERHAPS YOUR FATHER'S
SENDING YOU A MESSAGE,

1:09:43.246 --> 1:09:44.379
AN OLIVE BRANCH THAT--

1:09:44.381 --> 1:09:46.214
"LIFE IS SHORT."
OLIVER...

1:09:46.216 --> 1:09:47.448
OLIVER, THAT'S IT!

1:09:47.450 --> 1:09:48.750
[SLAPPING HIM]

1:09:48.752 --> 1:09:50.451
SHE WAS SENDING HIM
A MESSAGE!

1:09:50.453 --> 1:09:52.353
RITA! NORMAN!

1:09:52.355 --> 1:09:54.556
LET'S GO!

1:09:56.325 --> 1:09:58.593
[♪]

1:10:00.329 --> 1:10:01.462
[SHANE]: THERE'S A REASON

1:10:01.464 --> 1:10:03.498
SHE NEVER WANTED HIM
TO FORGET THAT--

1:10:03.500 --> 1:10:05.266
IT WAS HER WAY
OF BREAKING THE RULES,

1:10:05.268 --> 1:10:06.834
A WAY FOR HIM TO FIND HER.

1:10:06.836 --> 1:10:08.403
SHE WAS SENDING HIM
A MESSAGE?

1:10:08.405 --> 1:10:10.338
"LIFE IS SHORT."

1:10:10.340 --> 1:10:12.574
FILTER FOR "KELLY."

1:10:12.576 --> 1:10:14.475
"KELLY AND CHARLIE..."

1:10:14.477 --> 1:10:17.478
KELLY-- KELLY S.

1:10:17.480 --> 1:10:19.280
YES! [STOMPS FOOT]

1:10:19.282 --> 1:10:22.717
OH! LOOK AT HER.
SHE WAS SO BEAUTIFUL.

1:10:22.719 --> 1:10:24.619
[NORMAN]: "CHARLIE,
IF YOU FIND THIS PAGE,

1:10:24.621 --> 1:10:26.721
"YOU MUST HAVE REALLY
WANTED TO FIND ME.

1:10:26.723 --> 1:10:28.389
"AND IN CASE I DON'T
MAKE IT TO THE BRIDGE,

1:10:28.391 --> 1:10:29.657
"I WANTED YOU TO HAVE
THESE PICTURES

1:10:29.659 --> 1:10:31.793
TO REMEMBER THE LAST
BEST DAY OF MY LIFE."

1:10:31.795 --> 1:10:33.428
THERE'S CHARLIE
BY THE LAKE.

1:10:33.430 --> 1:10:34.662
THERE HE IS
SAILING THE BOAT.

1:10:34.664 --> 1:10:36.764
WHAT ABOUT CHARLIE
AND THE BLOODMOBILE?

1:10:36.766 --> 1:10:37.899
THEY HAVE TO BE
IN THE SAME PICTURE

1:10:37.901 --> 1:10:39.500
IN ORDER
TO ESTABLISH TIME AND PLACE.

1:10:39.502 --> 1:10:41.636
OKAY, THERE HE IS,
SWINGING ACROSS THE CREEK,

1:10:41.638 --> 1:10:42.804
LANDING ON
THE OTHER SIDE,

1:10:42.806 --> 1:10:44.372
THERE HE IS RUNNING.

1:10:44.374 --> 1:10:46.407
NO, THAT'S THE JOGGER
THAT RAN INTO CHARLIE!

1:10:46.409 --> 1:10:47.842
NO, WAIT.
OR IS THAT CHARLIE?

1:10:47.844 --> 1:10:49.644
NO. THAT'S THE JOGGER. IT JUST
SORT OF LOOKS LIKE CHARLIE.

1:10:49.646 --> 1:10:51.379
IT LOOKS A LOT
LIKE CHARLIE.

1:10:51.381 --> 1:10:53.715
SAME HAIR, SAME BUILD.

1:10:53.717 --> 1:10:55.316
SO CHARLIE WAS
KNOCKED DOWN BY SOMEONE

1:10:55.318 --> 1:10:56.517
WHO LOOKED
A GREAT DEAL LIKE HIM.

1:10:56.519 --> 1:10:58.686
RIGHT BEFORE
HE LOST HIS WALLET.

1:11:03.792 --> 1:11:06.527
[♪]

1:11:18.440 --> 1:11:20.408
[♪]

1:11:20.410 --> 1:11:22.310
THERE! THERE HE IS!
HE'S ON THE MOVE.

1:11:22.312 --> 1:11:25.313
WELL, GET IN!
COME ON.

1:11:25.315 --> 1:11:27.949
[♪]

1:11:32.521 --> 1:11:33.655
OLIVER, CAN'T THIS THING
GO ANY FASTER?

1:11:33.657 --> 1:11:35.657
MY FOOT'S ALL THE WAY DOWN.

1:11:38.360 --> 1:11:40.328
-OH, HE'S OVER THERE!
-OW.

1:11:40.330 --> 1:11:41.729
OKAY, HERE WE GO.

1:11:41.731 --> 1:11:43.931
-OH! LOOK OUT!
-SORRY!

1:11:43.933 --> 1:11:45.400
THERE HE IS--1:00.

1:11:45.402 --> 1:11:48.469
HANG ON, RITA!

1:11:49.705 --> 1:11:51.439
HEY! HO!

1:11:51.441 --> 1:11:52.640
YOU JERK.

1:11:52.642 --> 1:11:53.841
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1:11:53.843 --> 1:11:54.942
SORRY, SIR.

1:11:54.944 --> 1:11:56.611
THE 18th HOLE IS
CURRENTLY OFF-LIMITS

1:11:56.613 --> 1:11:58.513
DUE TO SOME SUSPICIOUS
GROUND SQUIRREL ACTIVITY.

1:11:58.515 --> 1:11:59.814
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?

1:11:59.816 --> 1:12:00.848
A MOMENT OF
YOUR TIME, JERRY.

1:12:00.850 --> 1:12:01.883
WHO ARE YOU PEOPLE?

1:12:01.885 --> 1:12:03.851
LOYAL AMERICANS DEDICATED

1:12:03.853 --> 1:12:05.553
TO THE HIGHEST STANDARD
OF MAIL DELIVERY.

1:12:05.555 --> 1:12:07.922
WE HAVE SOME INFORMATION
OF THE UTMOST IMPORTANCE

1:12:07.924 --> 1:12:08.990
WE WANT TO BRING
TO YOUR ATTENTION.

1:12:08.992 --> 1:12:10.625
I GOTTA SINK THIS PUTT

1:12:10.627 --> 1:12:12.460
AND BE BACK IN COURT
IN HALF AN HOUR.

1:12:12.462 --> 1:12:15.563
WE HAVE
A DOUBLE-DOUBLE REUBEN ON RYE

1:12:15.565 --> 1:12:16.798
FROM THE MILE-HIGH DELI

1:12:16.800 --> 1:12:18.800
THAT SAYS YOU WANNA HEAR
WHAT WE HAVE TO SAY.

1:12:18.802 --> 1:12:20.401
[OLIVER]: YOU ARE
THE PUBLIC DEFENDER

1:12:20.403 --> 1:12:22.001
FOR MR. CHARLES RIGGS,

1:12:22.003 --> 1:12:24.872
AND THIS IS THE INFORMATION
THAT PROVES HE IS INNOCENT.

1:12:25.674 --> 1:12:27.475
YOU'RE THE GUY
THAT CALLED ME.

1:12:27.477 --> 1:12:29.944
PHOTOS TAKEN THE SAME DAY
THE CRIME TOOK PLACE.

1:12:29.946 --> 1:12:33.915
NOTE THE BLOODMOBILE,
A ONCE-A-YEAR AFTERNOON EVENT.

1:12:33.917 --> 1:12:35.683
PLEASE PAY PARTICULAR ATTENTION
TO THIS PHOTO

1:12:35.685 --> 1:12:38.820
OF A MAN WHO BEARS
A REMARKABLE RESEMBLANCE

1:12:38.822 --> 1:12:40.788
TO MR. CHARLES RIGGS.
PLEASE NOTE HIS HAND

1:12:40.790 --> 1:12:43.558
SUSPICIOUSLY CLOSE TO
MR. RIGGS' BACK POCKET.

1:12:43.560 --> 1:12:44.692
I SUBMIT TO YOU

1:12:44.694 --> 1:12:45.827
THAT HE IS STEALING
THE VERY WALLET

1:12:45.829 --> 1:12:47.795
THAT THE MURDERER
OF ROGER PIPERSON

1:12:47.797 --> 1:12:49.497
PURPOSELY DROPPED AT
THE SCENE OF THE CRIME--

1:12:49.499 --> 1:12:50.732
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

1:12:50.734 --> 1:12:52.533
I KNOW IT SEEMS
A BIT FAR-FETCHED,

1:12:52.535 --> 1:12:53.601
UNTIL I POINT OUT
TO YOU

1:12:53.603 --> 1:12:56.571
THE MAN ACCOSTING
MR. RIGGS,

1:12:56.573 --> 1:12:57.872
REMOVING HIS WALLET,

1:12:57.874 --> 1:12:58.906
IS EUGENE MOSSLEY,

1:12:58.908 --> 1:12:59.907
THE COUSIN

1:12:59.909 --> 1:13:01.843
AND SOLE
LIVING RELATIVE

1:13:01.845 --> 1:13:02.977
OF THE DECEASED
MILLIONAIRE.

1:13:02.979 --> 1:13:05.413
LOOK HIM UP.
HE'S ON THE INTERNET.

1:13:05.415 --> 1:13:06.514
OH.

1:13:06.516 --> 1:13:07.782
FOLLOW THE MONEY,
MR. POLEVICH,

1:13:07.784 --> 1:13:09.584
AND I IMAGINE YOU WILL
FIND THE MURDER WEAPON

1:13:09.586 --> 1:13:12.487
AND A MAN WHO HAS JUST
INHERITED THE MILLIONS

1:13:12.489 --> 1:13:14.655
HIS COUSIN HAD
PROMISED TO AN ORPHANAGE.

1:13:14.657 --> 1:13:17.058
OKAY, WELL,
I'M GONNA GIVE, UH, ALL THIS

1:13:17.060 --> 1:13:18.860
SOME REAL THOUGHT.

1:13:18.862 --> 1:13:22.063
NO. YOU'RE GONNA GIVE THAT
TO THE DISTRICT ATTORNEY

1:13:22.065 --> 1:13:23.598
AND YOU'RE GONNA GET

1:13:23.600 --> 1:13:24.632
THE CHARGES AGAINST
MR. RIGGS DROPPED.

1:13:24.634 --> 1:13:25.733
IMMEDIATELY.

1:13:25.735 --> 1:13:27.735
WHAT IS THAT?
SOME KIND OF THREAT?

1:13:27.737 --> 1:13:29.570
NO.

1:13:29.572 --> 1:13:31.539
BUT THIS IS.

1:13:31.541 --> 1:13:33.708
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN
WHAT HAPPENS TO MONTANA STEAKS

1:13:33.710 --> 1:13:36.744
WHEN THEY'VE BEEN REROUTED
FOR ADDITIONAL POSTAGE?

1:13:38.580 --> 1:13:41.582
[TAKES A DEEP BREATH, SIGHS]

1:13:43.986 --> 1:13:46.854
WELL PLAYED, SIR.

1:13:51.693 --> 1:13:54.162
[♪]

1:14:03.071 --> 1:14:04.839
THAT'S RIGHT, PARKER.

1:14:04.841 --> 1:14:06.707
THE REMARKABLE WAY
IN WHICH THIS NEW EVIDENCE

1:14:06.709 --> 1:14:07.975
CAME TO LIGHT

1:14:07.977 --> 1:14:09.877
CERTAINLY CONTRIBUTED
TO RIGGS' SPEEDY RELEASE,

1:14:09.879 --> 1:14:13.881
WHICH WE EXPECT TO TAKE PLACE...
ANY MINUTE NOW.

1:14:14.950 --> 1:14:16.517
SO THIS IT?

1:14:16.519 --> 1:14:19.120
IT'S REALLY OVER?

1:14:19.122 --> 1:14:21.022
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,

1:14:21.024 --> 1:14:23.958
WE'LL BE BACK AT THE D.L.O.,
PACKING OUR PROVERBIAL BAGS,

1:14:23.960 --> 1:14:26.727
AND TRANSFERRING TO PUEBLO.

1:14:26.729 --> 1:14:29.831
OR MEEKER.
OR EAST TINCUP.

1:14:30.999 --> 1:14:33.835
OUR DAYS OF RULE-BREAKING
GLORY ARE OVER.

1:14:33.837 --> 1:14:35.803
NOT FOR ME.

1:14:35.805 --> 1:14:37.538
NO.

1:14:37.540 --> 1:14:40.675
I IMAGINE YOU'LL ALWAYS
BE FOUND SOMEWHERE

1:14:40.677 --> 1:14:42.810
STEPPING ACROSS A LINE.

1:14:42.812 --> 1:14:46.581
BEFORE IT'S ALL OVER,
I'D LIKE TO KNOW WHY.

1:14:46.583 --> 1:14:50.151
SHANE McINERNEY, WHY ARE YOU
SUCH A REVOLUTIONARY?

1:14:50.153 --> 1:14:52.653
WELL...

1:14:52.655 --> 1:14:55.089
SINCE YOU CALLED ME
BY MY REAL NAME,

1:14:55.091 --> 1:14:58.226
I'M GOING TO TELL YOU,
MR. O'TOOLE.

1:14:59.895 --> 1:15:01.863
I ALWAYS FOLLOWED
THE RULES.

1:15:01.865 --> 1:15:03.664
DROVE THE SPEED LIMIT.

1:15:03.666 --> 1:15:05.967
ALWAYS PARKED AT LEAST
FIVE FEET AWAY

1:15:05.969 --> 1:15:07.168
FROM THE FIRE HYDRANT.

1:15:07.170 --> 1:15:09.837
NEVER TORE THE TAGS
OFF FURNITURE.

1:15:14.176 --> 1:15:16.177
SO...

1:15:16.179 --> 1:15:21.115
ONE NIGHT, WHEN
I WENT TO A HOSPITAL,

1:15:21.117 --> 1:15:22.550
AND THEY TOLD ME

1:15:22.552 --> 1:15:23.885
THAT VISITING HOURS
WERE OVER,

1:15:23.887 --> 1:15:27.021
I SAID "THANK YOU.
I WILL COME BACK TOMORROW."

1:15:28.056 --> 1:15:30.157
BUT WHEN TOMORROW CAME...

1:15:31.827 --> 1:15:35.062
I DIDN'T HAVE ANYONE
TO COME BACK TO.

1:15:35.064 --> 1:15:39.967
MY DAD HAD DIED
IN THE NIGHT,

1:15:39.969 --> 1:15:44.672
AND I NEVER GOT TO THE CHANCE
TO WORK THINGS OUT WITH HIM.

1:15:45.908 --> 1:15:48.643
YOU TWO
WERE AT ODDS?

1:15:49.645 --> 1:15:54.582
HE HAD CALLED
A COUPLE OF MONTHS BEFORE,

1:15:54.584 --> 1:15:56.083
AND SAID THAT HE WAS SICK

1:15:56.085 --> 1:15:58.653
AND HE WANTED TO SPEND
MY BIRTHDAY WITH ME

1:15:58.655 --> 1:16:00.988
BEFORE HE DIED.

1:16:00.990 --> 1:16:03.157
I SAID...

1:16:03.159 --> 1:16:05.860
THAT HE HAD BEEN GONE SO LONG,

1:16:05.862 --> 1:16:08.963
THAT HE WAS
DEAD TO ME ALREADY.

1:16:14.102 --> 1:16:15.636
BUT HE WAS YOUR DAD.

1:16:15.638 --> 1:16:17.939
I'M SURE HE KNEW
YOU DIDN'T MEAN IT.

1:16:19.708 --> 1:16:22.243
HE KNEW THAT I DID.

1:16:23.812 --> 1:16:25.880
INTERESTING.

1:16:25.882 --> 1:16:27.949
WHAT?

1:16:28.984 --> 1:16:34.021
YOU MAY HAVE SURMISED BY NOW,
UH, I AM A MAN A FAITH.

1:16:34.023 --> 1:16:36.624
IT'S TRUE.
HE SINGS IN THE CHURCH CHOIR.

1:16:36.626 --> 1:16:37.858
TENOR.

1:16:37.860 --> 1:16:40.928
YOU MAY FIND MY FAITH

1:16:40.930 --> 1:16:43.264
AMUSING OR NAIVE,

1:16:43.266 --> 1:16:46.968
BUT YOU'RE SOMETHING
OF A BELIEVER YOURSELF.

1:16:46.970 --> 1:16:48.135
WHAT ABOUT ME

1:16:48.137 --> 1:16:49.770
COULD POSSIBLY GIVE YOU
ANY INDICATION

1:16:49.772 --> 1:16:51.639
THAT I BELIEVE IN GOD
AND REDEMPTION

1:16:51.641 --> 1:16:52.974
AND ALL THAT STUFF?

1:16:52.976 --> 1:16:54.976
WELL, IF YOU DON'T,

1:16:54.978 --> 1:16:57.912
YOU SHOULD THROW
THAT CARD AWAY RIGHT NOW.

1:16:57.914 --> 1:17:00.147
GO AHEAD.

1:17:00.149 --> 1:17:03.718
YET THERE IT IS,
STILL IN YOUR PURSE.

1:17:07.222 --> 1:17:10.758
YOU'RE HOPING
THERE'S REDEMPTION IN THERE.

1:17:10.760 --> 1:17:11.958
YOU'RE HOPING THAT

1:17:11.960 --> 1:17:16.964
THERE'S SOMETHING MORE THAN $20
IN THAT ENVELOPE.

1:17:17.733 --> 1:17:20.234
YOU'RE HOPING...

1:17:20.236 --> 1:17:22.203
THAT WHEN YOU
FINALLY FIND THE COURAGE

1:17:22.205 --> 1:17:24.972
TO TRUST THAT YOUR FATHER
NEVER STOPPED LOVING YOU,

1:17:24.974 --> 1:17:30.077
AND YOU TEAR OPEN THAT PAIN
YOU'VE BEEN CARRYING AROUND,

1:17:30.079 --> 1:17:33.080
THERE'S FORGIVENESS INSIDE.

1:17:36.218 --> 1:17:40.021
AND HOPE LIKE THAT,
MY DEAR SHANE...

1:17:42.691 --> 1:17:45.292
...IS WHAT
FAITH IS ABOUT.

1:17:50.932 --> 1:17:52.933
[DOOR LOCK BUZZING]

1:17:55.937 --> 1:17:57.972
[♪]

1:17:57.974 --> 1:17:59.306
[REPORTERS SHOUTING]

1:18:02.778 --> 1:18:04.078
HOW DOES IT FEEL
TO BE EXONERATED?

1:18:04.080 --> 1:18:06.814
WHAT'S THE FIRST THING
YOU'RE GOING TO DO?

1:18:06.816 --> 1:18:08.115
[REPORTERS ASKING QUESTIONS]

1:18:15.223 --> 1:18:18.092
[♪]

1:18:18.927 --> 1:18:22.363
I KNOW IT DOESN'T
MATTER NOW,

1:18:22.365 --> 1:18:24.765
BUT I JUST FIGURED,
IT'S THE 26TH,

1:18:24.767 --> 1:18:25.966
AND ONE OF US SHOULD
BE HERE, RIGHT?

1:18:25.968 --> 1:18:29.103
OF COURSE.

1:18:30.238 --> 1:18:32.106
WE GOT YOU

1:18:32.108 --> 1:18:33.207
A BAGEL AND LOX.

1:18:33.209 --> 1:18:34.809
UH, AND, UH
CREAM CHEESE AND CAPERS.

1:18:34.811 --> 1:18:37.011
THANKS.

1:18:37.013 --> 1:18:39.814
FOR... EVERYTHING.

1:18:43.251 --> 1:18:45.119
HEY, NORMAN, WE SHOULD
GO FEED THE DUCKS.

1:18:45.121 --> 1:18:46.253
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW.

1:18:46.255 --> 1:18:48.255
NORMAN.

1:18:48.257 --> 1:18:50.324
DUCKS CARRY DISEASE,
YOU KNOW.

1:18:53.895 --> 1:18:56.263
U.S. POSTAL SERVICE, HUH?

1:18:56.265 --> 1:18:59.033
AN OBSCURE DIVISION.

1:18:59.035 --> 1:19:01.102
WELL, THANK YOU.

1:19:01.104 --> 1:19:03.337
I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE THESE.

1:19:10.145 --> 1:19:12.012
AND A SEWING KIT.

1:19:12.014 --> 1:19:13.881
A SMALL SOUVENIR
I HAPPENED TO KEEP

1:19:13.883 --> 1:19:16.150
FROM THE WASHINGTON, D.C.,
HOLIDAY INN.

1:19:16.152 --> 1:19:19.220
SOMETHING TO REMEMBER US BY.

1:19:20.956 --> 1:19:23.424
[♪]

1:19:24.960 --> 1:19:26.427
GOOD LUCK, CHARLIE.

1:19:33.068 --> 1:19:35.369
[♪]

1:19:38.106 --> 1:19:40.074
IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE

1:19:40.076 --> 1:19:42.943
THIS IS OUR LAST ASSIGNMENT
TOGETHER.

1:19:42.945 --> 1:19:46.280
THIS IS OUR FIRST ASSIGNMENT
TOGETHER, NORMAN.

1:19:46.282 --> 1:19:47.214
YEAH.

1:19:47.216 --> 1:19:49.917
I'M GONNA MISS US.

1:19:51.319 --> 1:19:53.387
[BIKE RATTLING]

1:19:53.389 --> 1:19:56.090
[♪]

1:19:56.092 --> 1:19:58.893
[QUIETLY]:
OLIVER, LOOK.

1:20:04.833 --> 1:20:06.167
KELLY?

1:20:06.169 --> 1:20:07.868
CHARLIE.

1:20:07.870 --> 1:20:09.236
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

1:20:09.238 --> 1:20:10.404
WELL, WE HAD
A DATE, RIGHT?

1:20:10.406 --> 1:20:11.939
I-I KNOW, BUT I--

1:20:11.941 --> 1:20:13.240
I TRIED TO FIND YOU,

1:20:13.242 --> 1:20:14.842
I DID FIND YOU,
AT THE RESEARCH CENTER,

1:20:14.844 --> 1:20:16.410
BUT THEY SAID
NOBODY SURVIVED THE TRIALS.

1:20:16.412 --> 1:20:18.179
I NEVER FINISHED
THE TRIALS.

1:20:18.181 --> 1:20:19.947
I ONLY SIGNED UP
BECAUSE IT WAS FREE.

1:20:19.949 --> 1:20:22.116
I-I WAS TOO AFRAID
TO GO HOME TO BOSTON

1:20:22.118 --> 1:20:23.350
AND ASK MY FOLKS FOR HELP.

1:20:23.352 --> 1:20:25.019
YOU WERE IN BOSTON
THIS ENTIRE TIME?

1:20:25.021 --> 1:20:27.421
MY PARENTS FOUND ME
THE GREATEST DOCTOR

1:20:27.423 --> 1:20:29.490
IN THE WORLD
AND I--

1:20:32.227 --> 1:20:34.195
OH, MY GOD.

1:20:35.263 --> 1:20:36.964
THAT IS KELLY,
RIGHT?

1:20:36.966 --> 1:20:39.066
YES, NORMAN,
I BELIEVE IT IS.

1:20:39.068 --> 1:20:40.167
I KNEW IT!

1:20:40.169 --> 1:20:43.037
I KNEW SHE COULDN'T
ACTUALLY BE GONE.

1:20:43.039 --> 1:20:44.505
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

1:20:44.507 --> 1:20:46.373
I THOUGHT SHE WAS
SUPPOSED TO BE, YOU KNOW...

1:20:46.375 --> 1:20:49.109
DON'T BELIEVE EVERYTHING
YOU READ ON THE INTERNET.

1:20:49.111 --> 1:20:50.477
THAT'S RIGHT.

1:20:50.479 --> 1:20:53.113
"THERE ARE MORE THINGS
IN HEAVEN AND EARTH," NORMAN,

1:20:53.115 --> 1:20:56.250
"THAN CAN BE DREAMT OF
IN YOUR PHILOSOPHY."

1:20:56.252 --> 1:20:58.485
[OLIVER AND SHANE]:
SHAKESPEARE.

1:20:59.955 --> 1:21:02.189
[♪]

1:21:09.030 --> 1:21:12.132
[OLIVER]:
<i>AUNT TILLY'S MISSING WILL,</i>

1:21:12.134 --> 1:21:15.069
<i>THE MISSING REGISTRATION FORM</i>
<i>OF THE CLASS REUNION,</i>

1:21:15.071 --> 1:21:17.037
<i>THE ODD RANSOM NOTE,</i>

1:21:17.039 --> 1:21:19.173
<i>THE FIRST LETTER FROM COLLEGE,</i>

1:21:19.175 --> 1:21:21.542
<i>THE LAST LETTER FROM IRAQ...</i>

1:21:21.544 --> 1:21:23.277
<i>I HAVE SEEN IT ALL--</i>

1:21:23.279 --> 1:21:25.279
<i>DEAD LETTERS BY THE THOUSANDS,</i>

1:21:25.281 --> 1:21:27.014
<i>EACH ONE A TINY PAPER VESSEL</i>

1:21:27.016 --> 1:21:28.916
<i>LADEN WITH GOOD NEWS,</i>
<i>OR ILL,</i>

1:21:28.918 --> 1:21:30.150
<i>PROFIT OR LOSS,</i>

1:21:30.152 --> 1:21:33.420
<i>LOVE OR PAIN.</i>

1:21:33.422 --> 1:21:37.024
<i>TOSSED ABOUT ON THE ROUGH SEAS</i>
<i>OF GOVERNMENT PROTOCOL,</i>

1:21:37.026 --> 1:21:39.326
<i>A SHIP</i>
<i>SEARCHING FOR ITS HARBOR,</i>

1:21:39.328 --> 1:21:42.062
<i>EACH ONE BEARING THE POWER</i>
<i>TO CHANGE SOMETHING,</i>

1:21:42.064 --> 1:21:43.062
<i>AND YET,</i>

1:21:43.164 --> 1:21:45.099
<i>EACH ONE</i>
<i>A DESTINY POSTPONED...</i>

1:21:45.101 --> 1:21:47.334
<i>UNTIL IT COMES TO US.</i>

1:21:47.336 --> 1:21:51.538
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
THIS IS AN EXCELLENT DAY.

1:21:51.540 --> 1:21:53.240
[NORMAN]:
GOOD MORNING, OLIVER.

1:21:53.242 --> 1:21:55.142
GOOD MORNING, NORMAN.

1:21:57.312 --> 1:21:58.445
"DISTRICT ATTORNEY EDWARDS

1:21:58.447 --> 1:22:00.281
"HAILED THE LOCAL
POST OFFICE BRANCH

1:22:00.283 --> 1:22:01.415
"AT ALAMEDA AND DOWNING

1:22:01.417 --> 1:22:03.050
"FOR THE SUPERLATIVE SERVICE

1:22:03.052 --> 1:22:05.019
"AND A HIGHLY-EFFICIENT
DEAD LETTER DIVISION.

1:22:05.021 --> 1:22:07.388
"THE BRANCH WAS ORIGINALLY
SLATED FOR CLOSURE,

1:22:07.390 --> 1:22:09.290
"BUT WILL NOW BE <i>EXPANDED</i>

1:22:09.292 --> 1:22:11.058
"TO RECEIVE
ALL MISDIRECTED LETTERS

1:22:11.060 --> 1:22:15.029
FROM THE WESTERN
AND MID-STATES REGIONS!"

1:22:15.031 --> 1:22:16.330
[DOORS SWING OPEN]

1:22:16.332 --> 1:22:17.498
McINERNEY!

1:22:17.500 --> 1:22:20.334
LOOKS LIKE
YOU RATE NOW.

1:22:20.336 --> 1:22:21.568
THAT TRANSFER
YOU PUT IN FOR

1:22:21.570 --> 1:22:23.337
CAME THROUGH EARLY,
AND YOU REPORT

1:22:23.339 --> 1:22:26.206
TO THE DIRECT LINE OPERATIONS
AT THE TERMINAL ANNEX IN...

1:22:26.208 --> 1:22:27.508
TWO HOURS.

1:22:27.510 --> 1:22:29.410
THANKS.

1:22:29.412 --> 1:22:31.578
DO YOU STILL
WANT IT?

1:22:33.214 --> 1:22:35.316
I THINK, UH...

1:22:41.990 --> 1:22:43.991
I THINK...

1:22:43.993 --> 1:22:46.260
I THINK
I NEED A CUP OF COFFEE.

1:22:46.262 --> 1:22:49.396
UM...

1:22:49.398 --> 1:22:51.498
GOOD COFFEE.

1:22:51.500 --> 1:22:53.701
EXCUSE ME.

1:22:59.407 --> 1:23:02.609
LOOKS LIKE YOUR "LOOP"
JUST GOT A LITTLE SMALLER.

1:23:07.549 --> 1:23:10.317
[SNIFFS]

1:23:14.589 --> 1:23:17.257
[♪]

1:23:21.296 --> 1:23:23.530
ASPEN CHAI TEA WITH FOAM.

1:23:23.532 --> 1:23:26.100
NEXT?

1:23:30.205 --> 1:23:32.439
[♪]

1:23:45.587 --> 1:23:48.355
[♪]

1:24:04.472 --> 1:24:06.673
[♪]

1:24:19.187 --> 1:24:21.522
[♪]

1:24:26.661 --> 1:24:29.196
[DOORS SWING OPEN]

1:24:29.198 --> 1:24:30.464
COME AND GET 'EM!

1:24:30.466 --> 1:24:33.400
I GOT THREE
SKINNY VANILLA LATTES

1:24:33.402 --> 1:24:35.302
AND ONE STEAMBOAT AMERICANO.

1:24:35.304 --> 1:24:38.672
WE HAVE A LOT OF MAIL TO SORT
THROUGH TODAY, PEOPLE, SO...

1:24:38.674 --> 1:24:41.175
THAT WAS VERY NICE OF YOU.

1:24:41.177 --> 1:24:44.745
WELL, I FOUND
AN EXTRA $20 IN MY PURSE.

1:24:46.648 --> 1:24:49.383
[♪]

1:25:06.434 --> 1:25:08.602
[OLIVER]: <i>YES,</i>
<i>THE THOUGHTFULLY-COMPOSED,</i>

1:25:08.604 --> 1:25:10.270
<i>WELL-CONSIDERED, ADDRESSED,</i>

1:25:10.272 --> 1:25:12.239
<i>STAMPED,</i>
<i>PROFESSIONALLY POSTMARKED,</i>

1:25:12.241 --> 1:25:14.575
AND PERSONALLY-DELIVERED LETTER

1:25:14.577 --> 1:25:17.578
<i>IS STILL THE GOLD-STANDARD</i>
<i>OF HUMAN INTERCOURSE.</i>

1:25:17.580 --> 1:25:19.513
<i>GOD IS IN HIS UNIVERSE,</i>

1:25:19.515 --> 1:25:22.316
<i>AND ALL IS RIGHT</i>
<i>WITH THE WORLD.</i>

1:25:22.318 --> 1:25:24.585
[♪]
